title: photoshop_flowey
body:
Enemy from [[Undertale]].  Often described as "[[eldritch abomination|Cthulhian]]": A massive amalgam of a creature combining plant and mechanical features, crowned by a TV or computer monitor showing either a red-eyed white face [[evil_grin|grinning crazily]], a [[film_grain|grainy]] and distorted humanoid head, or [[flowey_(undertale)|Flowey]] himself.

Listed in the game's credits by this name and the game's code as Flowey X.  Also called God Flowey or Omega Flowey by fans.

[b]Major Spoiler Warning[/b]
[spoiler]Omega Flowey is the [[alternate_form|alternate form]] of Flowey, taken after Flowey kills [[asgore_dreemurr|Asgore]] and absorbs the human souls Asgore had collected.  He is the final boss of the game's Neutral Route.[/spoiler]

h4. External links 

* Undertale Wiki article: http://undertale.wikia.com/wiki/Photoshop_Flowey

title: shin_shouryuuken
body:
The [b]Shin Shoryuuken[/b] (真・昇龍拳,"True Rising Dragon Fist") is a very powerful super combo/ultra combo move used by [[Ryu (street fighter)|Ryu]] and [[Gouken]] in the [[Street Fighter]] series. It consists of three highly damaging hits, the third launching the opponent sky high. If not hit up-close, it will instead hit up to sixteen times as an anti-air.

Started in [[street_fighter_III_(series)|Street Fighter III]] and later spread to the Capcom vs. games.

title: schuzrum-galluss
body:
A fictional manned combat robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[Gundam Unicorn]].

[b]AMX-101E Schuzrum-Galluss [/b]

A modification of the [[Galluss-J]] [[mobile suit]] from [[gundam_zz|The First Neo Zeon War]], the unit foregoes all ranged armament and excess armor for a set of twin spiked shields and chain mines reminiscent of the Kämpfer, becoming a dedicated close range assault type MS for the [[Neo Zeon]] [[full_frontal|Sleeves]].

* [[List of Gundam Mechas]]

title: galluss-j
body:
A fictional antagonist [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] franchise. It first appeared in the [[Gundam ZZ]] series from 1986.

[b]AMX-101 Galluss-J[/b]

A close quarters type [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[Haman Karn]]'s [[Neo Zeon]]. It had a limited array of possible ranged armament, but was mostly made with toughness and melee power in mind, as it was more often than not deployed as "cleanup crew" after an area bombardment by ranged units such as the [[Zssa]].

title: kinnikuman
body:
Manga series created by Yoshinori Nakai and Takashi Shimada under the name Yudetamago. Originally serialized in [[Weekly Shounen Jump]] from 28 May 1979 to March 1987 for 387 chapters and later collected in 36 volumes. It was adapted into two anime series: a 137-episode series that aired on NTV from 3 April 1983 to 1 October 1986, and a 46-episode series ([i]Kinnikuman: Scramble for the Throne[/i]) that also aired on NTV from 6 October 1991 to 27 September 1992, in addition to seven theatrical films (1984-1986) and a television special (7 April 1984).

After 24 years, it returned in [i]Shuu Play News[/i], Shueisha's web version of [i]Weekly Playboy[/i] on 28 November 2011. 

The series involves an intergalactic stand-off between various heroes and villains with [[wrestling]] as a center theme.

title: evil_neuro-sama
body:
Evil Neuro was the [[dark persona]] of [[Neuro-sama]] but is currently the "evil [[twins|twin]] [[sisters|sister]]". Her first appearance was on March 25, 2023.

She has [[red eyes]]; [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] with an [[ahoge]], [[hair between eyes|hair between her eyes]] and [[two side up|two side ups]] held by [[red ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon|hair ribbons]] with a [[skull hair ornament]], and a [[broken heart hair ornament|broken heart-shaped]] [[hairclip]]. She wears a [[school uniform]]: a [[black cardigan|black]] [[v-neck]] [[off-shoulder cardigan]] with [[long sleeves]] reaching [[sleeves past wrists|past her wrists]], with a [[red bowtie]] over a [[white shirt|white]] [[dress shirt]] and a [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt]]; [[uneven legwear]] with a [[black socks|black]] [[single sock|sock]], [[black socks|black]] [[single kneehigh|kneehigh]] and a [[bandaid on knee|bandaid on her knee]]; and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[loafers]]. Her accessories include a [[red bag|red]] [[duffel bag|gymbag]] or [[shoulder bag]], and many [[button badge|button badges]] in the shapes of a pizza, a heart, a drone and a turtle soup badge.

title: rodney_aran
body:
The father of [[Samus Aran]] and husband of [[Virginia Aran]], who died during the [[Space Pirate (metroid)|]] raid of planet K-2L. 

In one of the ending images of [[Metroid Fusion]] he is shown firing upon a [[Ridley]] that is about to fire his plasma breath at him, while in the [[Metroid]] manga he instead sacrifices himself to self detonate the Afloraltite in order to blow up all the raiding Space Pirates forces, including Ridley.

title: virginia_aran
body:
The mother of [[Samus Aran]] and wife of [[Rodney Aran]], who died during the [[Space Pirate (metroid)|]] raid of planet K-2L. 

In one of the ending images of [[Metroid Fusion]] she is shown protecting a young Samus while [[Ridley]] approaches charging his plasma breath, while in the [[Metroid]] manga she is able to just in time distract Ridley who was about to kill a young Samus,  allowing Samus to escape while instead herself getting killed by his plasma breath.

title: yamaha_attitude
body:
A series of [[bass guitar]]s designed and produced by [[Yamaha]] in early 90s. Originally envisioned as a signature model of Billy Sheehan, it later saw multiple production runs in various control layout, pickup and string configurations. Its body and headstock shapes are reminiscent of Yamaha's [[yamaha_pacifica|Pacifica]] electric guitars which were designed around the same time.

The original Attitude Limited featured a [[fender precision bass|P-style]] tweeter pickup in the middle of the body and a larger rectangular woofer pickup near the neck joint together with twin output jack for each pickup and scalloped frets, while other models were mostly 4 or 5 string [[PJ bass]]es.

h4. Examples

* !post #6497737: Attitude Special

title: ghost_miku_(project_voltage)
body:
A character design by [[take (takegarou)|]] for the [[Pokemon]] and [[Vocaloid]] collaboration [[Project Voltage]] that imagines [[Hatsune Miku]] as a Ghost-type Pokemon trainer.

Ghost Miku has [[pale skin]], [[yellow eyes]] and [[very long hair]] that [[gradient hair|goes]] from [[blue hair|blue]] to [[white hair|white]] at the ends. Her hair is styled as [[twintails]] with a couple locks reaching [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]]. Parts of her body appear as if they're [[glitch]]ing and her [[detached arm|arms]] and [[detached legs|legs]] seem to be detached from the rest of her body. She wears a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[grey shirt]], a [[white necktie]], [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[black sleeves]] with a [[print sleeves|print]] that [[sleeves past fingers|extend past her fingers]], a [[see-through skirt|see-through]] [[black skirt]] and [[black thighhighs]].

title: evan_peters
body:
Evan Thomas Peters (born January 20, 1987) is an American actor. He made his acting debut in the 2004 drama film Clipping Adam and starred in the ABC science fiction series Invasion from 2005 to 2006.
Peters gained wide recognition for playing multiple roles over ten seasons in Ryan Murphy's FX anthology series American Horror Story, from 2011 to 2021. His performance as a detective in the HBO crime miniseries Mare of Easttown (2021) won him a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor. For portraying the titular character in Murphy's Netflix miniseries Dahmer – Monster: The Jeffrey Dahmer Story (2022), he won a Golden Globe Award for Best Actor and was nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor.

In film, Peters has played a supporting role in the superhero film [[Kick-Ass]] (2010), and [[Peter Maximoff]] / [[Quicksilver (marvel)|]] in the [[X-Men film series]] (2014–2019). He also received a nomination for the BIFA Award for Best Supporting Actor for playing a rebellious student in the heist film American Animals (2018).

title: scarlet_witch
body:
Character from [[marvel|Marvel Comics]], real name [[Wanda Maximoff]]. Originally introduced in [[X-Men]] as a villain, she would later become a member of the Avengers.
She's a mutant with the ability to control probability, which later evolved into control over the powerful Chaos Magic.
She's the sister of [[Quicksilver (marvel)|]], and has ocassionally been depicted as [[Magneto]]'s daughter.

title: gaza-c
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Zeta Gundam]] from 1985.

The [b]AMX-003 Gaza-C[/b] is an early transformable [[mobile_suit|MS]] fielded by [[Haman Karn]]'s [[Neo Zeon]]. 

It was plagued by minor design flaws in its transformable frame and a rushed production due to Neo Zeon's low resources, but was sent into action anyway with satisfactory combat performance - the only major drawback being an incapacity of using the transformation system more than three times without breaking the fragile suit apart.

Refined into the more resilient [[Gaza-D]].

title: mononoke_hime
body:
[b]Princess Mononoke[/b] (Japanese: もののけ姫, [i]Mononoke-Hime/Monster Princess/Spirit Princess[/i]) is a 1997 Japanese animated epic historical [[fantasy]] film written and directed by [[miyazaki_hayao_(person)|Miyazaki Hayao]], animated by [[Studio Ghibli]] and produced by Suzuki Toshio.

"Mononoke" (物の怪?) actually is not a name, but a general term in the Japanese language for a spirit or monster. 

The film was first released in Japan on July 12, 1997, and in the United States on October 29, 1999.

Princess Mononoke is a period drama set specifically in the late Muromachi period of Japan but with numerous fantastical elements. The story concentrates on the involvement of the outsider [[Ashitaka]] in the struggle between the supernatural guardians of a forest and the humans of the Iron Town who consume its resources. 

h4. See also

* [[San (mononoke hime)|]]

title: justice_task_force_member_(blue_archive)
body:
A nameless female mob unit in [[Blue Archive]] who serves as a part of Trinity General School's [[Justice Task Force (blue archive)|]]. Despite her lack of distinctive characteristics she's managed to garner quite a following. For short she may be called 正実モブ ([i]Seiji Mobu[/i], "JTF Mob") or affectionately as モブちゃん ([i]Mob-chan[/i]).

The named members of the [[Justice Task Force (blue archive)|]] (with the exception of [[Koharu (blue archive)|]]) all share certain character design elements in common with Mob-chan. [[Ichika (blue archive)|]] is particularly close to them, both in terms of appearance and being most likely to interact directly with them. This has lead to a common joke that Mob-chan represents a "base form" that the other members have "evolved" from. As of Ichika's recent release, these mobs have [[red eyes]].

Carries either an [[EM-2]] or an [[L85]]-style [[assault rifle]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #9082226: Default (version from ToSchool)

title: s_gundam
body:
A fictional manned military giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam Sentinel]].
 
[b]MSA-0011 S Gundam[/b]

A heavily armored assault [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[Anaheim Electronics]]. Despite its resemblance to the [[ZZ Gundam]], the two were not related, with the S Gundam being more oriented towards use by conventional pilots, being furnished with INCOMs for the quasi-psycommu system and an auxiliary AI, ALICE, to help with controlling the behemoth. The S in its name stands for "Superior".

h4. Related MS development
* [[Ex-S Gundam]]
* [[Nero (Mobile Suit)]]

title: crossbone_gundam_x-1_full_cloth
body:
A fictional manned combat robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[Crossbone Gundam]].

[b]XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Full Cloth[/b]

A further enhancement of the [[Crossbone Vanguard]] [[Crossbone Gundam X-1]] after the "Skull Heart" modification. The Full Cloth additional package, made with everything the SNRI had left once it became clear that maintaining the Crossbones was no longer possible, added multiple armor plates equipped with thrusters all over the unit, as well as the Skull Head Units containing I-Field generators for maximum defense. 

It was piloted by [[Tobia Arronax]], the former pilot of the [[Crossbone Gundam X-3]], whose wild and aggressive fighting style fit the mighty Full Cloth perfectly.
other_names: クロスボーンガンダムX-1フルクロス

title: crossbone_gundam_x-2
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[Crossbone Gundam]]

[b]XM-X2 (F97) Crossbone Gundam X-2[/b]

The second of the customized Gundam type mobile suits developed for the [[Crossbone Vanguard]]. 

The X-2 was virtually identical to its brother, the [[Crossbone Gundam X-1]], with the exception of a customized [[Shot Lancer]] equipped with more machine gun barrels and its black and lilac finish, the personal colors of its pilot [[Zabine Chareux]].
other_names: クロスボーンガンダムX2

title: fazz_(gundam)
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[Gundam Sentinel]].

[b]FA-010A FAZZ[/b]

A prototype [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[Anaheim Electronics]] as a physical proof of concept for the hugely powerful Full Armor [[ZZ Gundam]]. While some of the weaponry either had its power toned down or, in the case of the head mounted Hi-Mega Cannon, removed entirely, the FAZZ retained the mighty double [[beam rifle]], was structurally stronger due to lacking a transformation/combination mechanism (which the [[Full Armor ZZ Gundam]] would also omit). 

It also possessed a gargantuan external hyper mega [[beam cannon]] capable of accurately hitting targets thousands of kilometers away and more destructive than a battleship's main battery.

title: mobile_suit
body:
[b]Mobile Suit[/b], often abbreviated as [b]MS[/b], is the name of the [[mecha]] in the [[Gundam]] series. It basically refers to any (mostly) humanoid giant robot (standing from about 15 to 20+ meters tall) that is piloted by a human soldier (aside from [[G Gundam]], which uses the term [b]Mobile Fighter[/b]).

Most mobile suits are humanoid-shaped, though there are some which are not, such as the [[BuCUE]] and [[LaGOWE]] from [[Gundam SEED]].

This term was first introduced in the first episode of the original Gundam series, [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979. [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]], creator and writer of the series, explained that the concept of a manned robot was inspired by the [[super robot]] shows of the 1970s that began with the [[Mazinger Z]] anime from 1972. The name is also a tribute to the [[Mobile Infantry]], a fictional military organization of [[space marine]]s that uses [[power armor]] in the novel [[Starship Troopers]] from 1959.

h4. See also
* [[mobile armor]]
* [[man machine]]

* [[List of Gundam mechas]]

title: ning_hai_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the Chinese light cruiser [i]Ning Hai[/i] in [[Azur Lane]]. Her name (甯海) means "peaceful sea".

Historically, she was patterned after [[Yuubari (Azur Lane)|]] but reduced in size due to budget constraints. Unfortunately, she (and her sister [[Ping Hai (Azur Lane)|]]) inherited the same seakeeping deficiencies as Yuubari and other treaty-skirting warships built by Japan in the interwar period, but the Chinese regarded these as acceptable tradeoffs since they had intended the Ning Hai-class for coastal and Yangtze river use.

title: ping_hai_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the second [i]Ning Hai[/i]-class light cruiser, [i]Ping Hai[/i], in [[Azur Lane]]. Her name (平海) means "amicable sea". 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] tied into [[twintails]] and an [[ahoge]], and [[red eyes]]. Her default outfit consists of an [[anchor hair ornament]], [[red dress|red]] dragon print [[China dress|cheongsam]] with a [[cleavage cutout]], a [[single thighhigh|single]] [[black thighhighs|black thighhigh]] on her left leg, [[side-tie panties|side-tie]] [[white panties]], and a [[white jacket]]. Her rigging consists of two hull pieces containing her 140 mm twin gun mounts and additional 76 mm [[anti-aircraft gun]]s. 

Historically, she was to be built in the Jiangnan Shipyard in Shanghai to plans supplied by the Japanese from building [[Ning Hai (Azur Lane)|]], but rising tensions between the two countries delayed her construction and completion to 1937. Also unlike her sister, [i]Ping Hai[/i] did not have a seaplane complement and carried smaller-caliber AA guns.

Character designed by [[Kinjo Kuromomo]], voiced by [[Kuno Misaki]].

title: m3gan
body:
A 2022 American science fiction horror film.

The film follows Gemma, a robotics scientist at a toy company who suddenly finds herself taking care of her eight year old niece, [[Cady (m3gan)|]], after her parents death in a car accident. Due to her inexperience with children, Gemma creates a child size human robot with artificial intelligence named [[M3gan (character)|]] to take care of her niece. However, as M3gan becomes more smarter, the robot becomes obsessed in protecting Cady against anyone who she sees as a treat, including Gemma herself.

The film would later get a sequel, M3gan 2.0, in 2025, where Gemma is forced to work together with M3gan by building her a new body after a military robot that used the same technology as M3gan goes rogue and kills anyone that help in her creation which includes Gemma and Cady.

h4. External links

* "Official website":https://www.m3ganmovie.com/

title: ark_royal_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of HMS [i]Ark Royal[/i] (pennant number 91) in [[Azur Lane]].
Character design by [[mkiiiiii]], voiced by [[Itou Asuka]].

h4. Appearance

She has short-cut [[black hair]] and [[blue eyes]], and her rigging bears a steampunk theme, with her flight deck sporting multiple pipes and funnels.

h4. Personality
Ark Royal is notorious for her pathological obsession with destroyers (often [[mutsuki_(azur_lane)|Mutsuki]] and [[kisaragi_(azur_lane)|Kisaragi]]), to the point of flat-out pedophilia, outdoing even [[nagato (kancolle)|Nagamon]]. Many of her lines will reference destroyers and her feelings towards them, and she will treat marriage to the player as a means to the end of gaining access.

For her retrofit form, see her [[Ark Royal (retrofit) (azur lane)|corresponding page.]]

title: dazzle_paint
body:
Dazzle camouflage, also known as razzle dazzle or dazzle painting, was a type of ship camouflage used extensively in World War I and to a lesser extent in World War II. It consists of a series of highly contrasting color bands or angular shapes, often black and white, set at irregular angles. The purpose of dazzle camouflage is not to conceal or obscure a target, but to confuse visual spotting and range-finding so it cannot be effectively attacked.

Classic dazzle camouflage notable appears on the turrets of Kantai Collection's [[haruna (kancolle)|Haruna Kai Ni]]. The camouflage used by [[zuikaku (kancolle)|Zuikaku]], [[zuihou (kancolle)|Zuihou]], [[chitose (kancolle)|Chitose]] and [[chiyoda (kancolle)|Chiyoda]] is sometimes called dazzle camouflage, though its function was different, in that it was intended to disrupt and disguise the ships' flight decks. 

h4.See also

* "Wikipedia entry":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dazzle_camouflage
* Related pixiv tag: "ダズル縞パン":http://www.pixiv.net/search.php?word=%E3%83%80%E3%82%BA%E3%83%AB%E7%B8%9E%E3%83%91%E3%83%B3&s_mode=s_tag_full - the equivalent danbooru search is {{dazzle_paint striped_panties}}

title: donquixote_family
body:
An organisation in [[One Piece]]. Led by [[Donquixote Doflamingo]], the Donquixote Family (also known as the Donquixote Pirates) are a powerful group in the underground, supplying weapons and ruling Dressrosa with an iron fist.

They are mainly organized into groups named after the card suits. Doflamingo had intended for [[Trafalgar Law]] to take on the role of Corazon (heart), but Law had other plans.

[b]Commando Unit:[/b]

* Leader: [[Pica (one piece)|]] (Spade)
* [[Gladius (One Piece)|Gladius]]
* [[Buffalo (One Piece)|Buffalo]]

title: viola_(one_piece)
body:
[[One Piece]] character. Also known as Violet. She works for the [[donquixote_family|Donquixote Pirates]] as an assassin and officer of the [[Trebol (one piece)|]] Army. 

[spoiler]She is actually the daughter of King [[Riku Dold III]] and [[Scarlett (one piece)|]]'s younger sister and aunt of [[Rebecca (one piece)|]].[/spoiler]

Having consumed the Giro Giro no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], she has various eye-based powers.

body:

Having consumed the Hobi Hobi no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], she can turn people into living toys. Additionally the power has stopped her aging, leaving her physically a [[loli|small child]].

title: shiryuu_(one_piece)
body:
[[One Piece]] character. Nicknamed "Shiryu of the Rain". He is a member of the Blackbeard Pirates, serving as [[Marshall D. Teach|Blackbeard]]'s right-hand man.

[spoiler]Formerly the head jailer of [[Impel Down]], his position was revoked by [[Magellan (one piece)|]] for his excessive violence against prisoners subsequently resulting in his imprisonment and death sentence. However, Magellan released him temporarily to quell the prison riot perpetrated by [[Monkey D. Luffy]]. However, he goes against his superior's orders and exacerbated the riots by joining the Blackbeard Pirates and murdering the other guards.[/spoiler]

title: eleven_supernova
body:
In [[One Piece]], the term Supernova (or Super Rookie) refers to [[Pirate]]s whos bounties exceed 100 million before leaving the first half of the grandline. For better or worse, their strength tend to shape events around them.

[b]The Eleven Supernova:[/b]

Eleven Super rookies that all appeared at roughly the same time. Along with [[Marshall D. Teach|Blackbeard]], they're considered the "Worst Generation".
* [[Eustass Kid]]
* [[Monkey D. Luffy]]
* [[Basil Hawkins]]
* [[X Drake]]
* [[Trafalgar Law]]
* [[Scratchmen Apoo]]
* [[Killer_(One_Piece)|Killer]]
* [[Jewelry Bonney]]
* [[Capone Gang Bege]]
* [[Roronoa Zoro]]
* [[Urouge]]

[b]Other Generations:[/b]

Rookies from earlier or later years. While not as notorious, they're not to be taken lightly.
* [[Cavendish (one piece)|]]
* [[Bartolomeo]]
* [[Caribou_(One_Piece)|Caribou]]
* Coribou

title: cavendish_(one_piece)
body:
[[One Piece]] character. "Pirate Prince" Cavendish of the White Horse is the captain of the Beautiful Pirates.

He is a master swordsman carrying a named blade, Durandal. A bit of an attention whore, he has a grudge against the "Worst Generation" for stealing his spotlight in the papers.

title: trafalgar_law
body:
[[One Piece]] character. One of the [[Eleven Supernova]] and captain and doctor of the Heart Pirates. He became one of the [[Shichibukai]], but his position was revoked for allying with [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]].

Occasionally seen with close friend and crewmate [[Bepo (one piece)|]], though it is unknown exactly if Bepo is his first mate or not.

Having consumed the Ope Ope no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], he can create a "room" where he can separate and spatially displace anything and everything within it. This includes the ability to [[body switch|switching the body]] of his victim by exchanging their soul or detach/attach their limbs at his wish. Due to this ability, he is nicknamed "Surgeon of Death" for his combination of medical and combat skills.

Sometimes drawn alongside the [[Straw Hat Pirates]]' doctor [[Tony Tony Chopper]]. He is also often [[genderswap (mtf)|genderswapped]] as [[Law-chan]] due to an episode where Law and his crews were infected by a "feminization virus" which caused them to be temporarily transformed into women, which was perpetrated by [[Doc Q]].

It was later revealed that Trafalgar Law's [spoiler]full name[/spoiler] is [spoiler]Trafalgar D. Water Law[/spoiler], making him [spoiler]one of the carriers of the legendary "Will of the D."[/spoiler]
other_names: トラファルガー・ロー

title: pseudo-tokyo_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] worn by the attendees of the high school in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Id (fate/grand order)|]] chapter. If a character other than one of the ones depicted wearing it in Id is wearing it, the [[cosplay]] tag should also be added.

Students wear a [[red necktie]], [[white shirt]], [[black jacket|black]] [[blazer]], and either a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[grey skirt]] or [[pants]]. Some students also wear a [[blue vest|dark blue]] [[sweater vest]].

title: ready_or_not
body:
[b]Ready or Not[/b] is a tactical first-person shooter [[video game]] developed and published by [[Ireland]]-based VOID Interactive and released for [[Microsoft Windows]]. 

The player assumes the role of the leader of a [[police]] [[S.W.A.T.]] team in the fictional city of Los Sueños, California, which is tasked with dealing with organized/violent crime and hostage crises in the city. The game is known for its realistic, slow-paced gameplay, occasional [[horror_(theme)|horror]] themes and high degree of violence.

title: miku_collar_bikini
body:
A drawing trend based on either [[maud0239]] or [[channel (caststation)|]]'s drawing of [[Hatsune Miku]] in a striped bikini but with her collar, [[necktie]], and [[detached sleeves]] still worn as well.

Channel's drawing has Miku wearing a very [[crop top|cropped]] version of her white shirt with a [[micro bikini]]. Maud's version has her wear only the [[detached_collar|collar]] of her grey shirt, as well as [[Kagamine Rin]] likewise wearing only the [[sailor collar]], [[neckerchief]], and [[arm warmers]] of her own outfit.

Channel's art was posted in November 2023, months earlier before the trend began. But after Maud posted their art in June 2024, Channel "replied":[https://twitter.com/_CASTSTATION/status/1797961117282828612] to it with a repost of their own version, saying they wanted this kind of Miku to start trending, and thus it did.

* !post #6908324: [[channel (caststation)|]]'s version
* !post #7670286: [[maud0239]]'s version

title: oncidium
body:
An [[Orchid]] genus. Also known as dancing lady orchid. They have bulbous stem that emerge as it matures, elliptical to lanceolate leaves, and thin aerial roots. Their flowers have three sepals, two petals, and one oversized labellum that is reminiscent to a skirt-wearing person hence the name.

title: astral_express_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
The Astral Express is a large [[train]] that serves as one of the main settings of [[Honkai: Star Rail]] operated by the Nameless. It is powered by Akivili, the Aeon of the Trailblazer.

In the past, the Astral Express was first bestowed by Akivili. Shortly after the fall of the Aeon, the Nameless took upon Akivili's trailblazing legacy. When the Stellaron began to spread, the Star Rail also fell victim under its influence to the point where the train could barely function at all. As a result, the Nameless faction decided to abandon it after the rails have long been obstructed.

The Astral Express was later discovered by [[Himeko (honkai: star rail)|]] during her childhood, during which she became fascinated about the stories of the engine. She would repair the train years later to begin her journey across the universe.

In-game, it serves as the location for the Memory of Chaos endgame mode via the [[Messenger (Honkai: Star Rail)|]] as well as the [[gacha|Warp]] feature.

title: prey_(2022_movie)
body: Prey is a 2022 American science fiction action horror film, directed by Dan Trachtenberg and written by Patrick Aison. It is the fifth installment, and seventh overall including the crossover movies, of the [[Predator (series)|]]. The story takes place chronologically before the previous movies and serves as a prequel, as it is set in the Northern Great Plains in 1719. It stars Amber Midthunder, Dakota Beavers, Dane DiLiegro, Michelle Thrush, Stormee Kipp, Julian Black Antelope, and Bennett Taylor. The story revolves around a young Comanche woman, Naru, who is striving to prove herself as a hunter. She finds herself having to protect her people from a vicious, humanoid alien that hunts humans for sport, as well as from French fur traders who are destroying the buffalo they rely on for survival.

title: buruma
body:
A type of [[underwear]]-like gym shorts, typically worn as part of a [[gym uniform]] with a [[gym shirt]].

"Buruma" is an English-to-Japanese-to-English transliteration of the word "bloomer", usually identifying an over-panty or public garment, whose purpose is to cover the panty and crotch area while leaving the maximum maneuvering room.

In real life, buruma are rarely part of a [[gym uniform]] these days since they're considered old-fashioned; however, they still show up in anime since they are fetishized by otaku.  

The buruma has become a feature internationally in women's [[track and field]] and other sports uniforms. Though the design and materials may be different, the "racing buruma" as they are known in Japan, serve the same purpose and have the same brief shape. 

Contrast with [[bloomers]], which are a type of underwear constructed much like boxer shorts worn by women.

title: tacet_mark_(wuthering_waves)
body:
Special [[body markings]] found on all [[Wuthering Waves]] Resonators and throughout SOL3 (the game's world). All Resonators can channel power through their Tacet Mark to exhibit a power called a Forte. The release design of Tacet Marks resemble a sound wave diagram in line with the game's focus on sound-related themes, whereas its original design looked closer to a stretched-out star.

Note that Tacet Marks can vary in their activation state, appearance and location on a character's body but keep the same basic structure. Visit each character's individual wiki for more information on where to find their specific Tacet Marks.

[b]Note:[/b] [[Shorekeeper (wuthering Waves)|]] sets a precedent where some playable resonators may [i]not[/i] have a Tacet Mark. Only tag Tacet Mark on characters that show the current design or confirm with the character tag wiki for information on the location, if applicable, of a Tacet Mark.

h4. Examples

* !asset #20831947: Tacet Mark
* !post #7794195: Active Tacet Mark running down [[Jinhsi (Wuthering Waves)|]]'s back.
* !post #7595024: Inactive Tacet Mark on [[Male Rover (Wuthering Waves)|]]'s right hand.
* !post #7916341: [[Sanhua (Wuthering Waves)|]]'s right iris and pupil are a Tacet Mark.

She retains the red eyes of her [[Herrscher Of Sentience|Herrscher of Sentience]] form, but her hair now turns into [[two-tone hair|two-tone]] [[white hair|white]] and [[red hair|red]]. Her outfit consists of a [[black sports bra]] and [[black shorts|black]] [[short shorts]], a while cloth piece with a [[tassel]], [[red gloves]] with [[claws]], scarlet-colored [[feathers]] on her chest, and phoenix-themed [[red footwear|red]] [[thigh boots]].

title: jingwei_(bird)
body:
A recurring character across the [[Honkai (series)|]] franchise.

The bird that commonly appears alongside [[Fu Hua]] and the [[Herrscher Of Sentience|Herrscher of Sentience]] in [[Honkai Impact 3rd]] and [[Sushang (Honkai: Star Rail)|Sushang]] in [[Honkai: Star Rail]].

[b]In Honkai Impact 3rd[/b], it mostly shows up in events and can appear in four different ways:

* !post #4892797: Naked, completely white, with black eyes and red tips; associated with Fu Hua
* !post #4666784: Clothed with red eyes, can sometimes appear with black glasses, associated with the Herrscher of Sentience
* !post #4799112: Naked, completely white, with one eye covered and green tips; associated with the [[Fu Hua (Azure Empyrea)|Azure Empyrea]]
* !post #6640267: The [[Fu Hua (Phoenix)|Celestial Phoenix]]

[b]In Honkai: Star Rail[/b], the bird appears in two forms:

* !post #8125350: Sushang's Ultimate and on her phone case (pictured)
* !post #8125352: Qinqque's bird motif and hair ornament

Other names include:
* Chic
* Chic Phoenix
* Dark Chic Phoenix (Herrscher of Sentience's version only)
* Pyo
* Jingwei Bird
* Chicken
* Phoenix (used by Sushang in HSR)

title: reverse_bunnysuit
body:
A [[meme attire|memetic]] [[reverse outfit]] that resembles a [[Playboy bunny]] outfit, but with bare skin in place of the leotard. The torso is bare while the arms and legs are covered, resulting in negative space resembling a leotard where the leotard would normally go.

Other aspects of the [[Playboy bunny]] outfit are still normally present, including [[rabbit ears]], a [[rabbit tail]], [[fishnet thighhighs]], [[pantyhose]] or [[latex legwear]], [[wrist cuffs]], a [[detached collar]], and [[high heels]]. The leotard is usually replaced by a [[shrug (clothing)|shrug]] or [[cropped jacket]], with [[pasties]] occasionally covering the [[nipples]]. The pantyhose becomes [[hiphighs]], with [[maebari]] or [[strapless bottom]] occasionally covering the [[pussy]].

Originally first found in 2014 (post #1766182), but went viral in 2020. It's not exactly known what's the picture that began the meme, but it can be safely assumed that post #3701575 is the one that put most of the spark, given its popularity on both Twitter and Pixiv. 

A sub-meme was created by [[Touhou]] fanartists, featuring [[Usami Renko]] and [[Maribel Hearn]]; usually the artwork features Renko wearing a reverse bunnysuit with bunny pasties, while Maribel is in the background, accompanied with the description "Renko working at a shady part-time job recommended by a friend" (友人に勧められた怪しいバイトに勤しむ蓮子ちゃん).

h4. See also

* [[playboy bunny]]
** [[male playboy bunny]]
* [[meme attire]]
* [[reverse outfit]]

title: marx_(kirby)
body:
The main antagonist and final boss in [[Kirby Super Star]] and its remake, [[Kirby Super Star Ultra]]. Marx tricked [[Kirby]] into finding [[Galactic Nova]] so he could make his wish to have ultimate power and take over Popstar. After this, Marx turns into [[Marx (true form) (Kirby)|his true form]]. After his defeat, he returns in The True Arena as [[Marx Soul]], the last of the Final Four in said sub-game.

He makes a return in [[Kirby Star Allies]] as a Dream Friend. He is part of the first wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[Rick_(kirby)|]], [[Kine_(kirby)|]], [[Coo_(kirby)|]], and [[Gooey (kirby)|]].

He also appears as a boss in [[super_smash_bros.|Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]].

h4. External links

* "Kirby Wiki: Marx":[http://kirby.wikia.com/wiki/Marx]

title: family_guy
body:
Family Guy is an American animated sitcom created Seth MacFarlane for the Fox Broadcasting Company.
The show centers around the Griffins, a dysfunctional family consisting of parents Peter and Lois, their children, Meg, Chris, and Stewie, and their anthropomorphic pet dog, Brian. Set in the fictional city of Quahog, Rhode Island, the show exhibits much of its humor in the form of metafictional cutaway gags that often lampoon American culture.

title: archetype_inception_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]奏章Ⅲ 新霊長後継戦 アーキタイプ・インセプション[/b]

The surprise third Ordeal Call in [[Fate/Grand Order]] centered on the MoonCancer class. Its map location is Dubai on the Bleached Earth. [spoiler]It actually takes place on the lunar city of Moon Dubai in 3017 in a different timeline.[/spoiler] It initially released as a limited-time event taking place directly after [[Celeb Summer Experience!]] before being made permanently available.

Released in three parts on the Japanese server on August 28, 2024, September 11, 2024, and September 20, 2024, before being permanently released on February 1, 2025. Players are able to choose between [spoiler][[Kishinami Hakuno (Female) (MoonCancer)|]] and [[Kishinami Hakuno (Male) (MoonCancer)|]][/spoiler] as a reward for completing the ordeal call.

title: cameron_bloom
body:

title: gundam_f91
body:
[b]Mobile Suit Gundam F91[/b] (Japanese: 機動戦士ガンダムF91フォーミュラ ナインティワン, Hepburn: [i]Kidou Senshi Gandamu Foumyura Nainti Wan[/i], [b]Mobile Suit Gundam Formula 91[/b]) is a 1991 anime film set in the [[Gundam]] universe. 

It was written and directed by [[mobile_suit_gundam|original Gundam]] creator [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]]. It was Tomino's attempt to launch a new U.C. Gundam saga, set 30 years after [[Char's Counterattack]]. He re-teamed with character designer [[Yasuhiko Yoshikazu]] and [[mecha]] designer [[Ookawara Kunio]]  for the occasion.

Originally planned as a full-length television series, Gundam F91 hit a production snag due to staff disputes, and the project was stopped after the screenplays for the first thirteen episodes were written. It was then decided that what was made of the show would be condensed into a theatrical feature. The film was first released in [[Japan]] on March 16, 1991.

Set in [b]U.C. 0123[/b] (44 years after [[mobile_suit_gundam|the original Gundam]]), the story of Gundam F91 revolves around teenage space colonist [[Seabook Arno]], his girlfriend [[Cecily Fairchild]], and the efforts of the [[Crossbone Vanguard]] militia to establish an aristocracy known as "Cosmo Babylonia". In keeping with Gundam tradition, the civilian Seabook is forced by circumstance to pilot the [[F91 Gundam]], coincidentally designed in part by his estranged mother, Dr. [[Monica Arno]].

Chronologically continued by [[Crossbone Gundam]] and [[Victory Gundam]].

h4. See also
* [[Gundam F91 Formula Report 0122]]

h4. External links
* "Official Film OP":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cYH899IzY9g

title: fuun_karakuri_illya-jou
body:
[b]Illya's Karakuri Castle ~Kashin Koji's Modest Ambition~[/b]
[quote]Master and company start up the combat simulator for some training. But what appears before them is a castle filled with mischievous—and quite dangerous—obstacles and challenges devised by Sitonai!

"I changed the simulator into a Bounded Field. You have to complete all the challenges to get out, so good luck!"

A minute Singularity that has the potential to kill you... Its name: Illya's Karakuri Castle!

Faced with obstacle courses built under the supervision of an expert in illusions, will Master and their companions be able to overcome each stage of the challenge and safely reach the goal!?

A new kind of competitive festival, crowded with Chaldea's Servants...begins now![/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on May 24, 2023, and on the NA server on April 24, 2025.

title: lilim_harlot
body:
[b]Spiral Proof World: Lilim Harlot ~A Rose Without Ovation~[/b]
[quote]An alarm warning of imminent enemy attack echoes throughout Chaldea. This attack comes not from the outside, but bears the marks of contaminated magical energy coming from within. Unbelievable, the magical energy suggests its source is an Evil of Humanity—a Beast.

Chaldea races to destroy the source of this magical energy, but in the battle against the Beast, Master is suddenly Rayshifted. When Master comes to, they find themself in a dilapidated theater. Before Master fully comes to terms to the situation in which they find themself, a little girl calling herself "Draco" appears and says:

"Here's your answer. You are Master to me, a Beast."

In a "proof world" established by the bonds formed by Heroic Spirits, the curtain rises on a new story of the Holy Grail.[/quote]

A limited time collaboration event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] with [[Fate/Grand Order Arcade]], released on the Japanese server on April 26, 2023 and on the NA server on March 28, 2025. [[Setanta (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: may_the_4th
body:
An informal commemorative day, called Star Wars Day, is observed annually on May 4 to celebrate the [[Star Wars]] media franchise. It is a pun deriving from the phrase "May the Force be with you".

The following May 5 or May 6 is also recognized by some as "Revenge of the Fifth" or "Revenge of the Sixth" respectively to commemorate the villains of Star Wars.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Star Wars Day":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars_Day]
other_names: スター・ウォーズの日

title: chaldea_juukou_monogatari
body:
[b]The Story of Chaldea Heavy Industries ~Business to Business, From Me to You~[/b]
[quote]As Chaldea is caught up in the frenzy of White Day, a mysterious alert suddenly announces that a certain Singularity has reappeared.

"MISO Potato," "FUKAYA Green Onion," "Restoration Manjyu"... Delicious-sounding text appearing in the records triggers memories of the struggle that unfolded in the land from the past. And now, the man who brought so much chaos appears yet again to ignite another absurd corporate war.

Come, rise up from the depths, me! And come, my delightful employees! We're heading into a new age and everyone will see the grit and spirit it takes to be a Choushu man!

This tale is set in the Restoration City...a success story of you and me in SAITAMA.[/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on March 17, 2023 and on the NA server on March 5, 2025.

title: turn_a_gundam
body:
[i][b]Turn A Gundam[/b][/i] (stylized as [b]∀ Gundam[/b]) is a 1999 anime series written and directed by [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]] for the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]] series, marking his return to Sunrise after [[victory gundam|V Gundam]] in 1993.

Thousands of years into the future and in the aftermath of an ancient apocalyptic war, the "Earthrace" reverted to a Victorian-era lifestyle, while the more technologically advanced "Moonrace" went into cryostasis, waiting for the day they could repopulate the Earth, while occasionally sending advance scout parties to mingle with and spy on the Earthrace.

However, one such scout, [[Loran Cehack]], has since grew fond of the Earthrace, and when a Moonrace immigrant party began to stir trouble, Loran piloted the Turn A, a mobile suit worshipped as the "White Idol" by his adoptive nation, to not only prevent further conflict, but also bring peace between both races.

The series is notable because the peculiar looking hero [[mobile suit]] from the show and many other [[robot]]s were designed by an [[united_states|American]] artist ([[Syd Mead]]).

h4.See also

* [[Turn A Gundam (Mobile Suit)]]
* [[Turn X]]

* [[Orguss 02]] a 1993 mecha OVA with similar premise and [[steampunk]] setting.

title: elpeo_puru
body:
A fictional female character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]Elpeo Puru[/b] (also spelled [b]Elpeo Ple[/b]) is an [[orange hair]]ed young female character in Mobile Suit [[Gundam ZZ]], voiced by the late [[Honda Chieko]]. 

She is a [[Neo Zeon]] Newtype who piloted a custom [[Qubeley Mk II]] (colored purple) during "The First Neo Zeon War" (U.C. 088).

It is said that she was named after a magazine called "[[Lemon People]]" (L. People), hence the odd romanization of her name.

* [[Marida Cruz]]

body:

Riku starts using the Braveheart keyblade after [[Way to the dawn|his previous keyblade]] is broken in half by the Heartless in the Realm of Darkness. He leaves his old keyblade behind for his [[riku replica|other self.]]

title: way_to_the_dawn
body: The default form of [[Riku (kingdom hearts)|]]'s Keyblade, and appears in [[Kingdom Hearts II]], [[Kingdom Hearts II|Kingdom Hearts II Final Mix]], [[Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance]] and [[Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days]]. Like [[Kingdom key|Sora's Keyblade]], it is a Keyblade of the Realm of Light. Its form is based upon the [[Soul Eater (Kingdom Hearts)|Soul Eater,]] which it uses as an intermediary, and its name and design reflect Riku's nature as a being halfway between both light and darkness.

title: apryl_dyoa
body:
Apryl is an [[april fools|April Fools' Day]] character that surged in popularity on April 1st, 2025.

She has [[white hair]] [[two-tone hair|with]] a [[blue hair|blue]] [[colored inner hair|underdye]]. Her eyes are portrayed as either light [[blue eyes|blue]] or [[grey eyes|grey]].

She typically wears a [[white shirt]] with a [[necktie]] that matches her [[blue skirt|blue]] or [[black skirt]]. Her accessories include yellow [[triangle earrings]], blue [[fake animal ears]], an [[ID card]] with a yellow triangle on it, and a [[toeless legwear|toeless]] [[single sock|sock]] on her left leg. 

Many drawings of her include [[Illuminati]] imagery, such as a [[third eye]] on her forehead.

title: sanrio
body:
Sanrio Co., Ltd is a Japanese company that creates a range of (mostly) design series that features characters, and sells and licenses various products branded with these characters. These products include stationery, school supplies, gifts and accessories. Sanrio's best known character is [[Hello Kitty (character)|]], a white cat with red bow and no mouth. Hello Kitty is one of the most successful marketing brands in the world.

title: cathy_(hello_kitty)
body:
Retired [[Hello Kitty]] character, a white rabbit with a purple bow. Discontinued in 2011 due to legal issues caused by similarities to [[Miffy (character)|]].

Originally a precursor to [[Hello Kitty (character)|]] and one of [[Sanrio]]'s oldest characters, going by the name "Little Honey" in the 1970s (with a red bow), and briefly by "Daisy" (with a pink bow) in the 1990s.

title: persocom_(chobits)
body:
The human-like [[computer]]s from [[Chobits]], resembling humans with [[robot ears]] or some other robotic head ornament. They come in PC, laptop, and mobile sizes, and can do any task that a computer is needed for, such as browsing the web, sending email, and downloading programs. Their ears/head ornament can open up to reveal retractable cables, which can be used to plug them into a charging port or to transfer files.

title: super_robot
body:
[b]Super Robot[/b] (スーパーロボット [i]Sūpā Robotto[/i]) is an old genre of anime focused on giant [[robot]] [[mecha]] with various super powers, special and flashy weapons, and the cliche of attack/special move naming.

It originated from [[Tetsujin 28-Gou]] from the 1950s/1960s and the [[Mazinger Z]] series created by [[Nagai Gou]] in the early 1970s. While not as popular as it was during its beginnings, it still continues to this day. Can feature sentient robots in the same vein as [[Transformers]], like [[Astroganger]].

It evolved into the more realistic [b]"Real Robot":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mecha_anime_and_manga#Real_robot][/b] (リアルロボット, [i]Riaru Robotto[/i]) anime genre started by [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]]'s [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] in the late 70s and early 80s. This genre also continues to this day.

title: chaldea_yousei_kishi_hai
body:
[b]Chaldea Faerie Knight Cup ~The Next Generation's Triumphant Return~[/b]
[quote]A lone knight tasked with serving a certain queen arrived in Chaldea. But the queen no longer had a kingdom to rule, and so had no use for new retainers. And so, the knight's ambitions went unfulfilled...which is where it should have ended.

"Interesting. That knight doesn't look like the sort to give up once they've made up their mind. Fine. They seem like a good plaything worth break—I mean, testing! They'll have to prove their worth in physical trials, not just tests of mind and spirit!

And just like that, with Baobhan Sith's childlike glee, a secret training ground, the "Athletic Zone," is born in Chaldea's simulator!

To prove their skill and become an Expedition Faerie Knight in service to Her Majesty, the knight leaps into a competition in which heroes from all over the world vie to complete the Athletic Zone obstacle course.

The first ever Faerie Knight Cup is about to begin![/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on November 9, 2022 and on the NA server on November 8, 2024.

title: 108-nin_no_halloween_rebellion!
body:
[b]Fortress of the Jolly Banquet: Csejte Mount Liang[br]Halloween Rebellion of 108! ~A Dragon Girl's Water Margin~[/b]
[quote]Master and party depart to resolve a minute Singularity created by a Holy Grail. When they arrive, they encounter a small and mysterious(?) Servant covered in tattoos of nine dragons. This Servant is busily gathering outlaws and warriors to a place called Csejte Mount Liang.

The group believes the formation of the Mount Liang outlaw gang is the key to resolving the Singularity, but government forces stand in their way!

A fierce battle unfolds between the opposing groups as each pursues its own agenda. What lies ahead in the battle for the Mount Liang outlaws!?[/quote]

A limited time [[Halloween]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on October 12, 2022 and on the NA server on October 11, 2024. [[Eliza the Nine-Tattooed Dragon (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

[b]Illusionary Yamatai Continuum: Sakai[br]THE Great Tea Ceremony Battle: GUDAGUDA New Yamatai-koku, The Man Who Returned from Hell[/b]
[quote]Chaldea receives a distress call from the most unexpected of places: Yamatai-koku...only it should already have disappeared! The team traces the signal to a land where lost souls wander: the liminal space between the worlds of the living and dead.

What new encounters await? Or will this be a reunion with old, familiar faces?

When myriad threads of fate long past intersect, THE tea ceremony battle begins![/quote]

title: arctic_summer_world!
body:
[b]Demonic North Pole Theme Park: Arctic Summer World[br]Arctic Summer World! ~Chaldea's Magical Summer Theme Park~[/b]
[quote]Searing rays of sunshine and sweltering heat herald the arrival of summer. Will this year's summer be a vacation by the beach? A trip to the mountains? A grand treasure hunt?

No. Cookie-cutter summer plans are SO last year!

The usual midsummer Singularity appears, but this time in the arctic. Prepare for the ultimate embodiment of ice and chill! Was this part of someone's grand scheme, or is it some strange consequence of the summer heat? Whatever the cause, swimsuit-clad Servants travel one after the other to the Singularity, where a huge amusement park, themed after the Arctic Circle, is constructed!

A paradise it may be, but it remains a Singularity, and so there's only one thing Master needs to do...

Under the pretense of repairing the summer Singularity (also known as Operation Let's Enjoy Summer!), Master and party head to the Arctic Summer World![/quote]

A limited time [[Summer]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on August 10, 2022 and on the NA server on July 18, 2024. Players can choose between [[Ortlinde (Swimsuit Assassin) (fate)|]], [[Hildr (Swimsuit Assassin) (fate)|]], and [[Thrud (Swimsuit Assassin) (fate)|]] as a reward for completing the event.

title: nanmei_yumihari_hakkenden
body:
[b]Nanmei Yumihari Eight Dog Chronicles[/b]
[quote]One day, a little puppy wanders into Chaldea. The dog-loving Servants gather around in delight as the mysterious puppy capers about. After the initial excitement dies down, an unknown Servant arrives, claiming to be the puppy's owner. But something seems off about their Spirit Origin. Chaldea's staff begins an analysis of the Servant, but a tremendous roar and a sudden, accompanying tremor shake Chaldea violently.

Out of nowhere, a mysterious arrow smashes into Chaldea, causing massive damage. Master, along with a hastily assembled party, assembles to search the assailant before they can unleash their next devastating strike. Their search takes them to a newly discovered group of minute Singularities!

Will Master and company be able to locate and defeat their mysterious attacker before the next arrow strikes Chaldea!?[/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on June 29, 2022 and on the NA server on June 4, 2024.

title: mississippi_mythicizers
body:
[b]Serial Mythological Theater: Mississippi Mythicizers[/b]
[quote]As Master and Mash enjoy a rousing conversation about Bunyan and her tall tales, reports of a minute Singularity reach them. The target location? The Mississippi River basin in the early twenty-first century.

The group immediately sets out to investigate, only to encounter a treasure ship—the Takarabune of Japanese legend! And dinosaurs! And delightful companions! (Or a ridiculous lot...depending on how you look at it.) Chaos pours in from all ages, and at the center of it all, a new and different Bunyan makes herself known!

"Join me and become one of my delightful companions (employés) so we can create a new kind of myth!"

A curious tall tale journey to recover a Holy Grail begins!

And...action![/quote]

A limited time collaboration event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] with [[Learning with Manga! FGO]], released on the Japanese server on April 27, 2022 and on the NA server on April 19, 2024.

title: battle_in_new_york_2022
body:
[b]Battle in New York 2022 ~Space Odysseus Versus Nikola Tesla~[/b]
[quote]With the title of "strongest" on the line, the spectacular festival of valor has once again made its glorious return! The unexpected arrival of a goddess from the skies threw the last tournament into chaos. Now the host, the King of Heroes, is properly prepared in case the goddess interrupts once again. However...

"How do you do, people of Mid Earth 2033? I am the Great Space Adventurer...Space Odysseus!"

A massive Federation Space Force fleet suddenly appears! Nikola Tesla, head of tournament security, and the Holy Grail Coupled Hyper-Temporal Defense System are Earth's last line of defense against this new invader!

The starting bell rings once again in New York!

Formerly known as Battle in New York 2022, the GBF (Galactic Battle Festival) in New York begins now![/quote]

title: 15-nin_no_richiteki_na_megane-tachi
body:
[b]15 Bespectacled Intellectuals[/b]
[quote]"Okay, time to go fix yet another minute Singularity!"

Under Da Vinci's enthusiastic command, Chaldea heads to a minute Singularity in modern-day Europe, only to find themselves ambushed in an office building! The group can't see, smell, or in any way sense the presence of this mysterious enemy. Before they can even figure out how they are being injured, they hear an unfamiliar Servant's voice:

"The glasses! Put on a pair of glasses!!!"

Following the voice's instructions, every member of the group puts on the pair of glasses they are given. The instant they do, a Demonic Beast, fangs bared and ready to strike, appears before them! Wearing these mysterious glasses, the group employs their enhanced analytical skills and intellect to guide them in repairing the minute Singularity.

The spectacular battle, framing Master's future, begins now![/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on March 2, 2022 and on the NA server on March 1, 2024.

title: manannan_souvenir_valentine
body:
[b]Manannan's Souvenir Valentines: The Chocolate Tree and the Goddess's Choice[/b]
[quote]Valentine's Day is forever plagued with inexplicable complications. This year, everyone in Chaldea is on edge, hoping to avoid trouble, but a single Servant manifests amid the chaos, using it to their benefit, and it is those very precautions that allow this to happen. Before anyone notices the Servant disappears, and all that remains is a record of someone having Rayshifted. That could only mean one thing: an inside in Chaldea. But who would do such a thing?

"I may be the god of love, but I am also a nun... How could I not guide the lost sheep?"

The unrepentant messenger of love is responsible for the creation of yet another minute Singularity, and so the sweet, bitter, and admittedly bizarre story of a strange Valentine's Day unfolds.[/quote]

A limited time [[Valentine]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on February 9, 2022 and on the NA server on February 1, 2024.

title: making_christmas_party!
body:
[b]The Making of a Christmas Party![/b]
[quote]What is a witch? What is Santa Claus? After hearing Elizabeth's rather...unclear...definition, Scáthach-Skadi, having decided to become the ideal Christmas witch, sets off to find the perfect candidate for this year's Santa.

Santa Claus is...
According to one, Santa "cleanses! Sterilizes! Disinfects!"
While another tells her, "Santa is samba...a carnival, sí!"
Yet another says "I think, therefore I Santam"...

"I have transformed your Spirit Origin into Santa Claus! Now, it's time for you to spread Christmas joy in Chaldea!"

And so, by decree of Scáthach-Skadi, Martha, the holy maiden has become the newest Santa Claus. As to Martha's understanding of her duty as Santa Claus...

Come on! It's time for another crazy Christmas at Chaldea![/quote]

A limited time [[Christmas]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on December 8, 2021 and on the NA server on December 7, 2023. [[Martha (Santa) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: chaldea_summer_adventure!
body:
[b]Chaldea Summer Adventure! ~A Boy Pursuing Dreams and a Girl Who Dreams~[/b]
[quote]The dazzling sun, the blue sea, camping fun, delicious BBQ, and—what has become somewhat of a Summer tradition—the discovery of a minute Singularity.
This year's summer is set on the Caribbean islands, a location famous for pirates running amok in search of treasure.

"Some pirate supposedly left the ultimate treasure somewhere in the Caribbean..."

Thinking this secret treasure rumored amongst the pirates is the link to resolving the Singularity, Chaldea participates in a great Caribbean treasure hunt!

The golden age the pirates always dreamed of, combined with an ancient hidden treasure...another grand summer adventure in the romantic Caribbean Sea begins![/quote]

A limited time [[Summer]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on September 8, 2021 and on the NA server on August 31, 2023. [[Leonardo da Vinci (Swimsuit Ruler) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: nanachi_(made_in_abyss)
body:
[b]Nanachi[/b] is one of the main characters appearing in [[Made in Abyss]], voiced by [[Izawa Shiori]].

Nanachi looks like an [[furry|anthropomorphic]] rabbit with goat-like [[horizontal pupils]] and a long tail. Often seen wearing a [[horned helmet]]. The [[white hair]] and [[yellow eyes]] are unchanged from the human form. 

Nanachi lives with [[Mitty (made_in_abyss)|]] in the abyss, and has a habit of saying "nna" (んなぁ) in their speech.

This character's gender is [[androgynous|ambiguous]], and should be tagged as [[1other]] unless depicted with definitive [[genderswap (otm)|male]] or [[genderswap (otf)|female]] features.

h4. See also

* [[Nanachi (human) (made in abyss)|]]

title: the_lego_movie
body:
A 2014 American computer animated comedy movie by Warner Animation Group.

The plot revolves around [[Emmet Brickowski|Emmet]], an ordinary [[Lego]] minifig who one day finds the "Piece of Resistance" and, accompanied by [[Wyldstyle]] and a bunch of other Lego characters, must stop Lord Business from gluing everything in the Lego universe.

A [[The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part|sequel]] was released in 2019, while a spinoff was released in 2017 in the form of [[the LEGO Batman Movie]].

* "Wikipedia: The Lego Movie":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lego_Movie

title: susie_(kirby)
body:
A key character from [i][[Kirby: Planet Robobot]][/i] (Hoshi no Kirby: Robobo Planet).
She has [[pink hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. She pilots the [[Business Suit (kirby)|]] to battle, and uses the [[Transporter (kirby)|]] for air travel.

[spoiler]Her full name is a Susanna Patrya Haltmann (EN)/ Susanna Familia Haltmann (JP) and she is the daughter of President [[Max_Profitt_Haltmann|Haltmann]].[/spoiler]

She returns in [i][[kirby star allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i] as a Dream Friend. She is part of the third wave of post-launch Dream Friends along with [[Magolor]], [[Taranza]], [[francisca_(kirby)|Francisca]], [[flamberge_(kirby)|Flamberge]], & [[Zan Partizanne]].

h4.See also

* [[Kirby (series)]]

title: hyness
body:
The main antagonist of [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i]. He and his subordinates worship [[Void Termina]] for reasons unknown beyond an omnicidal revenge plot against an ancient civilization.

His appearance is concealed within a white [[robe]] with gold trimmings and long sleeves with a red interior. On his hood is an emblem associated with the Jambastion Mages and their subordinates. His face is hidden, with only glowing [[yellow eyes]] showing.

[spoiler]
When his hood is knocked off, his true appearance is revealed to be that of a blue imp-like creature with bulging chameleon-like eyes, ears similar to [[magolor|Magolor's]], and a big floppy nose. In this state, he shows a resemblance to [[Magolor]], [[squidward_tentacles|Squidward]] and [[Hypno]].
[/spoiler]

title: vividria
body:
One of the Mid-bosses that appear in [[Kirby Star Allies]]. She wears a dress and has a [[paintbrush]]-shaped [[ponytail]]. She may be swallowed by [[Kirby]] to obtain the [[artist_kirby|Artist]] [[copy ability|]], or befriended via a Friend Heart.
Vividria is heavily implied to have a connection to [[Drawcia]] from [[kirby: canvas curse|Kirby: Canvas Curse]] and [[Paintra]] from [[Kirby: Triple Deluxe|]].
H4. See also
* "Wikirby: Vividria":https://wikirby.com/wiki/Vividria

title: broom_hatter
body: A recurring enemy in the [[Kirby (series)|]] series. It has a yellow body without visible eyes, wears a [[witch hat]], and carries a [[broom]]. In [[Kirby's Dream Land 3]] and [[Kirby Star Allies]], [[Kirby]] can inhale it to gain the [[cleaning kirby|Cleaning]] [[copy ability]]. h4. See also * [[Keke (kirby)|]]

title: francisca_(kirby)
body: An antagonist in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i] and one of the Three Mage Sisters (the other two being [[flamberge_(kirby)|Flamberge]] and [[Zan Partizanne]]). The sisters, especially with their leader [[Hyness]], worship [[Void Termina]] for reasons unknown beyond an omnicidal revenge plot against an ancient civilization. [spoiler]Though that doesn't stop [[Kirby]] from reaching out to them...[/spoiler]

title: morpho_knight
body:
A secret boss in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i]. He is another masked knight that is themed after [[butterfly|butterflies]] and possibly [[valkyrie|Valkyries]], and is very heavily based on a design from the scrapped [i]Kirby[/i] game on the [[gamecube|GameCube]].

He appears at the very end of [i]Guest Star ???? Star Allies Go![/i], taking form after doing something with [[Galacta Knight]]. As such, his attacks consist of a mix of swordplay and magic.

[spoiler]He takes on a more powerful form called Morpho Knight EX at the end of the [[francisca_(kirby)|Three]] [[flamberge_(kirby)|Mage]] [[zan_partizanne|Sisters']] Guest Star run as well as near the end of Soul Melter EX.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]He reappears in the post-game campaign of [[Kirby and the Forgotten Land]], stealing the final boss spot from [[fecto_forgo|Soul Forgo]]. However, after Morpho Knight’s defeat, Forgo retakes the spot, using the DNA it absorbed from Morpho Knight to become [[Chaos Elfilis]].[/spoiler]

h4. See also
[[Morpho Knight (butterfly)]]

title: gooey_(kirby)
body:
A mysterious, goofy blob that first appears in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_2|Kirby's Dream Land 2]][/i]. He would replenish [[Kirby|Kirby's]] health upon being freed from the clutches of a mid-boss.

He later appears in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_3|Kirby's Dream Land 3]][/i], where he acts as Kirby's Player 2 companion during the adventure. 

He is a small blue blob with bulbous eyes, and can attack with his long [[tongue]], not unlike [[Yoshi]]. At some point in [i]Dream Land 3[/i], he is also seen with the same kind of orange petals/orbs as [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], further supporting the fact that he is a part of it that had turned good.

He makes a return in [i][[kirby star allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i] as a Dream Friend. He was part of the first wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[rick_(kirby)|Rick]], [[kine_(kirby)|Kine]], [[coo_(kirby)|Coo]], and [[marx (kirby)|Marx]].

title: galacta_knight
body:
A recurring boss character in the [i][[kirby_(series)|Kirby]][/i] series. He makes his debut in [i][[Kirby Super Star Ultra]][/i] at the very end of the [i]Meta Knightmare Ultra[/i] subgame, where [[Meta Knight]] summons [[Galactic Nova]] to wish for a fight against him. Since then, he has made various re-appearances as a secret superboss in future [i]Kirby[/i] games ([i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land]][/i], its [[kirby's_return_to_dream_land_deluxe|remake]] and [i][[Kirby: Planet Robobot]][/i] to be exact). In [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i], however, a "[[morpho_knight|fluttery fiend]]" absorbs him and is fought instead.

He is the strongest warrior in the galaxy in Kirby's world and was sealed away because he was deemed too strong. [spoiler]([[Star Dream]] even suggests that he may have destroyed at least one planet in the past). 

[spoiler]He also appears in [i][[Super Kirby Clash]][/i] as a true final boss, surprisingly enough. Here, he is dubbed "Aeon Hero", and counts with two powered-up forms -Light and Dark- that change his appearance. He is also implied to be one of the ancient heroes who sealed away [[Void Termina]] long ago, as he attacks using the spears of the heart that kept the Dark Lord in place.[/spoiler]
H4. External links
* "WiKirby: Galacta Knight":https://wikirby.com/wiki/Galacta_Knight
other_names: ギャラクティックナイト

title: brobo
body:
An obscure character from the [[Kirby (series)|]] series, which makes its first and only appearance as an enemy in [[Kirby's Block Ball]]. It is a circular creature that wears a [[robot]]-like armor.

Brobo would not feature in another game until [[Kirby Star Allies]], where it makes a cameo along with [[Gryll (kirby)|]] as a rare [[stone_kirby|Stone]] transformation.

title: driblee
body:
An enemy in the [[kirby_(series)|Kirby]] series, first appearing in [[Kirby Star Allies]]. It is based on an [[eel]].
[[Kirby]] can inhale and swallow Driblee to obtain the Water [[copy ability]], or befriend it by using a Friend Heart.

title: floaty_the_cell_core_(kirby)
body:
A water-based enemy from [[kirby star allies|Kirby: Star Allies]]. 

For more info, see the "wiki":[https://wikirby.com/wiki/Floaty_the_Cell_Core].

title: plugg_(kirby)
body: An enemy debuting in [[Kirby 64]], resembling a [[electric plug]]. Made an unexpected reappearance in [[Kirby Star Allies]].

title: con_(kirby)
body: One of a boss pair that appears in [[Kirby's Dream Land 3]] and [[Kirby Star Allies]]. It is a [[fox]] that is always found with [[Pon (kirby)|]].

title: zan_partizanne
body: An antagonist in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i] and the leader of the Three Mage Sisters (the other two being [[francisca_(kirby)|Francisca]] and [[flamberge_(kirby)|Flamberge]]). The sisters, especially with their leader [[Hyness]], worship [[Void Termina]] for reasons unknown beyond an omnicidal revenge plot against an ancient civilization. [spoiler]Though that doesn't stop [[Kirby]] from reaching out to them...[/spoiler]
other_names: ザン・パルルティザーヌ

title: void_soul
body:
The "Essence of Chaos", [[Void Termina]]'s core.

The boss that takes this name in particular is exclusive of the Soul Melter difficulty in [[Kirby Star Allies|"The Ultimate Choice"]], replacing a nameless version of Void Termina's core from the main story.

Void Soul themself is also replaced in [spoilers]Soul Melter EX (the highest difficulty) by [[Void (Kirby)|]][/spoilers]

title: ribbon_(kirby)
body:
A fairy from [[kirby_64|Kirby 64: The Crystal Shards]] who is a friend of [[Kirby]] and assists him in his adventure to find the shards of the fairies' prized crystal, which was shattered by [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]]. Ever since the game's true ending, she has also been shown to be a possible love interest of Kirby's.

She is also one of the few humanoid Kirby characters, and is one of the few Kirby characters to have a human-like face.

She also appears in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i] as a Dream Friend with [[Adeleine]] by her side. She is part of the second wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[Daroach]] and [[Dark Meta Knight]].

title: adeleine
body:
Adeleine is a friend of [[Kirby]] and an artist who is best known for her ability to bring her creations to life.

Much like [[paint_roller_(kirby)|Paint Roller]] back from [i][[Kirby's Adventure]][/i], she can use paintings for combat, most notably in her boss fights. Unlike Paint Roller, she can only be attacked after she runs out from her easel (though she goes down in one hit).

While she's better known for her appearance in [i][[Kirby 64]][/i], she's implied to make her debut earlier in [i][[Kirby's Dream Land 3]][/i] under similar circumstances and a different name ("[[Ado (kirby)|]]", due to name space constraints). Due to differences in design between the two games, some fans like to distinguish the two appearances despite them possibly being the same character, calling the [i]Dream Land 3[/i] design "Ado" and the [i]64[/i] design  "Adeleine". In some cases, the two designs are drawn as twins.

She also appears in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i] as a Dream Friend with [[ribbon_(kirby)|Ribbon]] by her side. She is part of the second wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[Daroach]] and [[Dark Meta Knight]].

title: kirby_star_allies
body:
A [[kirby_(series)|Kirby]] game for the [[Nintendo Switch]]. This is the latest in the "Return to Dream Land" series of games with the safe approach of traditional gameplay mechanics. The main attraction here is an expanded-upon co-op experience that allows up to three additional players to join in as Kirby recruits friends to his team with the new Friend Heart.

[[Kirby]] wakes up one day to notice that [[King Dedede]] is stealing food from Dream Land once again. Knowing that something is wrong with this picture, he immediately sets out to investigate. What follow is one of the grandest adventures he's ever been on, with the help of a lot of friends both old and new!

body: A crew of [[waddle_dee|Waddle Dees]] serving as reporters for Dream Land's news station. Initially Twitter-only characters, they have since gone on to appear in [i][[Kirby Battle Royale]][/i].

title: kirby_battle_royale
body:
A [[kirby_(series)|Kirby]] spinoff for the [[Nintendo 3DS]]. Unlike most other [i]Kirby[/i] games, this is mainly played from a top-down perspective like [[Kirby's Blowout Blast]]. It is a brawler game where up to four players pick a character or copy ability and duke it out in one from a selection of challenges.

[[King Dedede]] is feeling rather competitive, so he decides to host a fighting tournament. [[Kirby]] gladly accepts the invitation, but when he arrives, he finds the place filled with a bunch of clones of himself. With no other choice, Kirby and his partner [[Bandana Waddle Dee]] fight their way to the top!

h4. Characters

* [[Kirby]]
* [[Bandana Waddle Dee]]
* [[Meta Knight]]
* [[King Dedede]]
other_names: カービィバトルデラックス!

title: kingdom_hearts_dark_road
body:
Standalone expansion within "[[kingdom_hearts_x|KINGDOM HEARTS Uχ]] Dark Road" for mobile phones, and eleventh title of the [[KINGDOM HEARTS]] videogame series. Set some time after the Keyblade War and decades before [i][[kingdom_hearts_birth_by_sleep|Birth by Sleep]][/i], features the "[[xehanort|Young in Black]]" and "[[eraqus|Youth in White]]" introduced in [i][[KINGDOM HEARTS III]][/i] as the primary protagonists. Gameplay returns to the card-based display of the original [i]χ[chi][/i] with mechanics reminiscent of the "Flick Rush" minigame in [i][[kingdom hearts 3d: dream drop distance|Dream Drop Distance]][/i].

title: lea_(kingdom_hearts)
body:
A red-haired boy who first appears in [[kingdom hearts birth by sleep|Birth By Sleep]], alongside his best friend [[isa (kingdom hearts)|Isa]].

[spoiler]His Nobody is [[axel (kingdom hearts)|Axel]], but after Axel sacrificed himself to protect Sora during [[Kingdom Hearts II]], he returned to being Lea. Furthermore, he is shown to wield a Keyblade of his own in [[kingdom hearts 3d: dream drop distance|Dream Drop Distance]], much to everyone's surprise.

Not to be confused with his [[Axel_(kingdom_hearts)|Nobody]].

title: xehanort
body:
Character from the [[KINGDOM HEARTS]] videogame series. This tag is used for [[Master Xehanort]] in his teenaged years, or [b]Young Xehanort[/b]. This can refer to either of two appearances, both retaining the [[dark skin]] and [[grey hair|silver]]/[[white hair]] of his older incarnations:

1. The young man introduced in [i][[kingdom hearts 3d: dream drop distance|Dream Drop Distance]][/i] as an antagonist. Here he is dressed in a [[black coat (kingdom hearts)|]] and has yellow eyes. Alternatively known as "Young Master Xehanort".

2. A younger version seen in a flashback in [[kingdom hearts 3d: dream drop distance|3D]] and in [i][[KINGDOM HEARTS III]][/i] as the "Youth in Black", playing a game of [[chess]] against [[Eraqus]] (likewise the younger version of [[Master Eraqus]]). Both characters are the playable protagonists of [i][[kingdom_hearts_dark_road|Dark Road]][/i].

title: ansem_seeker_of_darkness
body:
[[Kingdom Hearts]] character. Refers to a character who is mentioned throughout [[Kingdom Hearts I]] as a wise man who compiled a series of reports detailing how to defeat the [[Heartless (kingdom hearts)|]].

[spoiler]He winds up being the main antagonist of the first game by possessing [[Riku (kingdom hearts)|]]'s body and seeking to open the door to the Realm of Darkness. In [[Kingdom Hearts II]], he is revealed to be [[Master Xehanort]]'s Heartless, and returns in [[kingdom hearts 3d: dream drop distance|Dream Drop Distance]] despite his earlier defeat.[/spoiler]

Not to be confused for [[Ansem the Wise]].

title: perara
body:
An enemy from [[kirby: squeak squad|Kirby: Squeak Squad]], Perara is a blue disk-shaped enemy with a slight bulge and single visible eye, usually seen floating in mid-air.

body:
A wand-like object that appears in [[Kirby: Squeak Squad]], initially used by [[Daroach]]. It damages enemies by firing up to three star-shaped projectiles. [[Kirby]] obtains it before fighting the game's final boss, [[Dark Nebula]].

title: animal_kirby
body:
A [[copy ability]] that appears in [[Kirby: Squeak Squad]] which lets [[Kirby]] [[digging|dig]] through [[dirt]].

In this form, Kirby wears a brown [[animal costume]] with a notable [[hood]] and [[claws|clawed]] [[paw gloves]] and [[paw shoes|feet]].

title: kingdom_hearts_3d:_dream_drop_distance
body: [[Nintendo 3DS]] game in the [[Kingdom Hearts]] series, written out as [i]KINGDOM HEARTS 3D [Dream Drop Distance][/i]. Set between [i][[Kingdom Hearts coded]][/i] and [i][[Kingdom Hearts III]][/i], focusing on [[sora_(kingdom_hearts)|Sora]] and [[Riku (kingdom hearts)|]] during their Mark of Mastery exams.

title: dark_nebula
body:
The true antagonist and final boss of [[Kirby: Squeak Squad]]. Its existence remains completely unknown until the endgame, where it is revealed that [[Meta Knight]] has kept its prison (a treasure chest that was thought to contain [[kirby|Kirby's]] strawberry shortcake) in captivity.

When [[Daroach]] stole the chest upon Kirby defeating Meta Knight, Dark Nebula immediately possessed the Squeak Squad leader and proceeded to carry out its evil plans. As expected, Kirby corrected his childish mistake by promptly laying the smackdown on the dark lord and saving the day once more.

It is heavily implied that Dark Nebula and [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]] are one and the same, especially with flavor text provided by a Japan-exclusive handbook from Kirby's 20th anniversary. This would explain its possession of Daroach, its association with darkness, and it having one eye

One of the primary antagonists of [i][[Kirby: Squeak Squad]][/i], Daroach is the leader of the titular "Squeaks", a team of bandits. He's a bipedal [[mouse (animal)|]] with [[claws]] and [[yellow eyes]] who wears a [[red_headwear|red]] [[top hat]] and [[red_cape|cape]].

h4. External links

title: pokemon:_magikarp_jump
body: Mobile game where you teach a [[Magikarp]] to jump high.

title: kirby_mass_attack
body:
[[Kirby (series)|]] game.

Ever wanted to control 10 Kirbies at once? No? Well, too bad! [[Necrodeus]] is having none of [[Kirby]] being alive, so he decides to split the puffball into 10 smaller ones so that he has an easier time picking them off. One manages to escape the carnage and decides to save Dream Land from this new crisis!

Also joining him are the returning Squeaks, with [[Daroach]] at the helm once more. This time, he gives hints and advice to help Kirby in his quest.

Like [[Kirby: Canvas Curse]], this game is entirely controlled with a touch screen in order to navigate all 10 of Kirby to safety. You don't have [[copy_ability|copy abilities]] this time around, so be careful!

h4. Characters

* [[Whispy Woods]]
* Lady Ivy
* [[King Dedede]]
* Skullord
* [[Necrodeus]]

title: drawcia
body:
The main antagonist of [i][[kirby: canvas curse|Kirby: Canvas Curse]][/i]. She is a [[witch]] who sought to turn Dream Land into a literal work of art. [[Kirby]] tried to beat her up, but she turned him into a ball, causing him to lose his limbs. Luckily, her paintbrush was having none of this, so it decided to team up with him to take down its crazy mistress!

While she initially appears as a more traditional witch, she shows [[drawcia_soul|her true(?) form]] after taking enough damage.

title: drawcia_soul
body:
The second and true(?) undead form of [[Drawcia]], fought at the very end of [[Kirby: Canvas Curse]]. Here, she is significantly more monstrous, being a giant orb with five [[yellow eyes]] and fighting [[Kirby]] through rather unorthodox methods compared to his previous foes.

Intentionally or not, she kicked off the trend of final bosses gaining a "Soul" form, among which are [[Marx Soul]], [[Magolor Soul]], [[Soul Of Sectonia]], [[star_dream|Star Dream Soul OS]], [[Void Soul]] (and possibly [[void_(kirby)| Void]]), and [[Chaos Elfilis]].

title: kirby's_epic_yarn
body:
The first [[Kirby_(series)|]] game on the Nintendo [[Wii]]. Not unlike [[Kirby: Canvas Curse]], this is not a conventional [i]Kirby[/i] game. Kirby is no longer able to suck things up and gain [[copy ability|copy abilities]] (as air passes through his now-made-of-yarn body), so he relies on a yarn whip to pull enemies to him and throw them at obstacles.

A [[Nintendo 3DS]] port released in 2019 called [[Kirby's Extra Epic Yarn]], which introduces some quality-of-life enhancements as well as new minigames featuring [[King Dedede]] and [[Meta Knight]].

h4. Characters

* [[Kirby]]
* [[Prince Fluff]]

h4. Bosses

* [[Fangora]]
* [[Hot Wings]]
* [[Squashini]]
* Capamari
* [[King Dedede]]

* [[Yin-Yarn]]
** Mega Yin-Yarn
