title: axel_(kingdom_hearts)
body:
Antagonist and major supporting character who first appears in [[kingdom hearts: chain of memories|Chain of Memories]]. He is the eighth member of [[Organization XIII]], using the element of fire and a pair of chakrams as his weapons.

[spoiler]He is the Nobody of [[lea (kingdom hearts)|Lea]], but after Axel sacrifices himself to protect Sora in [[Kingdom Hearts II]], he returns to being his original self.[/spoiler]

title: diz
body:
[[Kingdom Hearts]] character. DiZ is an acronym meaning 'Darkness in Zero'. A mysterious man who wears red bandages over his face. He guides [[Riku (kingdom hearts)|]] and [[Namine]] throughout the events of [[kingdom hearts: chain of memories|Chain of Memories]].

[spoiler]DiZ is actually [[Ansem the Wise]] after his apprentice Xehanort banished him.[/spoiler]

title: kirby_and_the_rainbow_curse
body:
The sole [[kirby_(series)|Kirby]] game for the Nintendo [[Wii U]], and a spiritual sequel to [[Kirby: Canvas Curse]]. Unlike the predecessor, this game forgoes [[copy_ability|copy abilities]] in favor of methodical puzzle solving and occasional transformations.

Kirby and friends were having fun in a clay-ful Dream Land one day. Suddenly a portal opens up! Out comes a magical force that sucks away all the color from Dream Land. Luckily, [[Bandana Waddle Dee]] fends off the new invader before it could defeat our puffy hero. Together with Bandana Waddle Dee and a paintbrush fairy named [[Elline (kirby)|]], Kirby sets out to bring color back to his world!

h4. Characters

* [[Kirby]]
* [[Bandana Waddle Dee]]
* [[Elline (kirby)|]]
* [[Whispy Woods]]
* [[The Claykken]]
* [[Hooplagoon]]
* [[Claycia]]
* [[Dark Crafter]]
other_names: タッチ!カービィスーパーレインボー

title: kingdom_hearts:_chain_of_memories
body:
Second game in the [[Kingdom Hearts]] action-JRPG series. Bridges [i][[kingdom hearts i|Kingdom Hearts]][/i] and [i][[Kingdom Hearts II]][/i]. Released on the [[Game Boy Advance]], and later PlayStation 2.

Because of character crossover, only use in certainty (such as exclusive characters or character interaction, or explicit confirmation).

title: kirby:_canvas_curse
body:
[[Kirby (series)|]] game.

Now this is a first! [[Kirby]] was relaxing one day when a witch named [[Drawcia]] suddenly appeared and turned all of Dream Land into a work of art, literally! Kirby tried to beat her up, but she turned him into a ball, causing him to lose his limbs. Luckily, her paintbrush was having none of this, so it decided to team up with him to take down its crazy mistress!

This game is unique in that it is controlled almost entirely with the DS' touch screen, where the player draws lines and taps on Kirby to help him navigate through levels.

h4. Characters

* [[paint_roller_(kirby)|Paint Roller]]
* [[Kracko]]
* [[King Dedede]]
* [[Drawcia]]

title: escargon
body: [[King Dedede]]'s [[snail]] servant who appears in the [[kirby: right back at ya!|Kirby: Right Back at Ya!]]. Escargon lived in a farm with his mother and sometime ago left home to make her proud and become king, but ended up being a lackey of the King. Siding with the King and often trying to help make his friend's plans work, which often fails, Escargon is just as rude and selfish as Dedede, and takes as much abuse as he dishes out, but deep down he's not so bad. He's also very smart, reading books and even developing machines and stuff.

title: waddle_dee
body:
A common enemy in the [[kirby_(series)|Kirby series]]. Waddle Dees are soldiers of [[King Dedede]] who are found everywhere in Pupupuland. Their basic action is to just walk and jump around, doing absolutely nothing harmful. There are many different kinds of Waddle Dees, especially wielding parasols. 

In the [[kirby: right back at ya!|anime]], they live in Dedede's castle and run errands for him but often goof up. There are many of them living in the castle, all led by a single [[Waddle Doo]].

h4. Notable Waddle Dees

* [[Sailor Waddle Dee]]

** [[Assistant Waddle Dee]]

** [[Reporter Waddle Dee]]

title: king_dedede
body:
King Dedede is the self-proclaimed king of Dream Land, [[kirby|Kirby's]] #1 rival, and a recurring antagonist in the [i][[kirby_(series)|Kirby]][/i] games. Typically caring only for himself, he likes to mess with others because he thinks it's fun. He even once stole all of Dream Land's food. However, Dedede isn't all bad - he's just more of a bully who pulls pranks on others just for the fun of it. Sometimes, he does do good deeds, and will even team up with Kirby more often than he'd like to admit.

In the [[kirby: right back at ya!|anime]], Dedede also pulls pranks on others and especially tries to make other people's lives as miserable as he can because he thinks it's fun. He buys monsters called [[Demon Beast|Demon Beasts]] created by the Holy Nightmare Company, led by [[Nightmare_(Kirby)|Nightmare]], to help him with his desires, and has a snail sidekick called [[Escargon]].

title: meta_knight
body:
Meta Knight is a popular character in the [[Kirby_(series)|Kirby series]] and is the second of [[Kirby]]'s rivals, the first being [[King Dedede]]. He follows a code of honor, often providing Kirby with a sword to battle with (only breaking that code when he's not in control of himself, or when the situation is dire), and fights using a golden spiked sword called [[Galaxia (sword)|]]. Meta Knight is also shown to help Kirby sometimes.
 
In the [[kirby: right back at ya!|anime]], he's definitely on Kirby's side, helping him fight against the evil Demon Beasts created by the Holy [[Nightmare (kirby)|]] Company that Dedede buys from them. He shows some relationships with one of Kirby's friends, [[Fumu (kirby)|]], seeing her as a rare source of intelligence. He's also a Star Warrior, having been one before Kirby and having been one of the few survivors of the war between the Galaxy Soldier Army and the Holy Nightmare Company. 

He is also playable in the [i][[Super Smash Bros.]][/i] games, starting with [i]Brawl[/i]. In [i]Brawl[/i] specifically, he is notorious for being a "god tier" character, which was addressed in the later [i]Smash[/i] games.

title: customer_service_(kirby)
body: A recurring villain in the [[kirby: right back at ya!|Kirby TV series]], and the public face of NightMare Enterprises, Customer Service sells monsters to [[King Dedede]] in order to further [[nightmare_(kirby)|his employer's]] efforts to conquer the universe.

title: whispy_woods
body:
A recurring boss in the [[Kirby (series)|]] series, Whispy Woods is usually the first boss enemy [[Kirby]] has to face in his adventures. He is known for being one of the easiest bosses for Kirby to fight - He's a (usually) stationary tree that drops apples on Kirby to attack, so all Kirby has to do is inhale the apples that drop and spit them back at him while standing next to him to avoid the air bullets he spits out. Whispy has appeared in many games ever since the very first one and sometimes takes a spot other than Level 1 in a game, and sometimes even changes strategy and gains new attacks, but that doesn't make him any tougher. A similar boss named King Golem who appears in Kirby & The Amazing Mirror also shares the same attack pattern as Whispy.

In the [[kirby: right back at ya!|anime]], Whispy takes a different role. Instead of being a major enemy, Whispy serves as an ally to Kirby and his friends. He is very kind to his friends, yet shows no mercy to those who threaten his kingdom and forest. At first, he thought Kirby and his friends were intruders and tried to crush them as punishment. But after realizing [[King Dedede]] used him, Whispy becomes Kirby's friend while Dedede tries many times to cut down his forest (yet fails every time). In the [[Super Smash Bros.]] games, Whispy appears in the background, often minding his own business before taking deep breaths and then blowing strong winds that push players close to the edges of the Kirby stages he is placed in.

For more info, see his "wiki page":https://wikirby.com/wiki/Whispy_Woods.

title: halberd_(airship)
body:
The Halberd is a giant flying battleship built and commanded by [[Meta Knight]] in the [[kirby_(series)|Kirby series]]. Debuting in [[Kirby Super Star]], it's initially used by Meta Knight in an (unsuccessful) attempt to conquer Dream Land. Since then, it has continued to serve as Meta Knight's main base of operations.
It also appears in the [[kirby: right back at ya!|anime]] as well as [[Super Smash Bros.]]

[spoiler]It's also [[kirby|Kirby's]] main weapon used to fight [[Star Dream]], courtesy of the [[Robobot Armor]][/spoiler]

title: bugzzy
body:
Bugzzy is a character in the [[kirby_(series)|Kirby series]].
He first appeared in [[Kirby's Adventure]].
He looks like a large [[stag beetle]]. He specializes in an attack in which he holds [[Kirby]] between his horns and then slams him down. It also releases [[ladybug|ladybugs]].
From him you can [[copy ability|copy abilities]] such as “[[Backdrop kirby|Backdrop]]” or “[[Suplex kirby|Suplex]]”.

In [[Kirby: right back at ya!|Kirby: right back at ya!]], Bugzzy does not use his horns, but a [[club (weapon)|club]] and large [[sword|swords]] in his hands.
Kirby couldn't [[inhaling|inhale]] Bugzzy, but he did get the [[Sword kirby|Sword]] by inhaling Bugzzy's sword.

title: neck_brace
body:
A protection for the neck.
The soft type looks like a bulky cloth collar and is designed to provide support after an injury, while the more recognizable rigid type is larger and is made with molded plastic to restrict neck movement during recovery from a fracture or surgery. 
Modified versions of the rigid-type brace are worn by athletes who participate in high-impact sports and auto racing to prevent injuries.

title: dagger
body:
A double-edged [[knife]] used for [[stab]]bing or thrusting. They are often a secondary defense [[weapon]] in close combat.

The difference between a dagger and a [[knife]] is that daggers are double-edged or edgeless and intended primarily or exclusively for stabbing, while knives are usually single-edged and intended primarily for cutting. Many knives and daggers are capable of either stabbing or cutting.

title: jaguarman_series
body:
[b]Jaguarman[/b] (ジャガーマン) is a [[Kemono Friends]] otoMAD that was uploaded in 2017, which paired Jaguar's scenes from Episode 2 of the first season with "Devilman no Uta" from the 1970s [[Devilman]] anime, sentence-splicing the vocals to fit the visuals. Two more videos were made, following up this otoMAD, using the openings from [[Shinzou Ningen Casshern]] and the 1969 [[Tiger Mask (series)|]] anime respectively. The thumbnails for each of these is Jaguar having her right arm raised.

The videos soon popped off on [[Niconico]], spawning derivative meme/[[neta]] videos, successors and so forth, developing into its own minor meme series. The Jaguarman Series explicitly refers to those which have Jaguar as the focal figure (or, more narrowly, the original three otoMADs), while branches such as Wakaruman (fusing [[Wakari Tetsuya]] with the Devilman part of the meme) don't have to necessarily have her in such a position. 

h4. Characters

* [[Jaguar (kemono friends)|]]
** [[Small-clawed Otter (kemono friends)|]] appears as well, due to appearing in the same episode used in the otoMADs.
* [[Skull Servant]] ([[Yu-Gi-Oh!]]), otherwise known as Wight (per the Japanese)
** Due to Skull Servant's sudden appearance in Jaguarman around 00:48, saying "ワイトもそう思います" ("Wight think so too"), leaving a strong impression, he has become a recognizable part of the series. He would be voiced by the preluding lines in [[Shinzou Ningen Casshern]]'s opening in derivative otoMADs.
* [[Tibetan Fox (kemono Friends)|]]
** A derivative video, "Tibesunaman":[https://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm32332253], would use all three associated themes for the first time in a medley format, in the same order as the series, among other things accredited to it. Tibetan Fox, in turn, is sometimes associated with the series.
* The Good Friend Trio: [[Devilman (character)|]], [[Casshern]], and [[Tiger Mask (character)|]]
** Following several developments within the scene, following their themes' association with the original three videos, the three were dubbed the Good Friend Trio and made into their own characters, voiced by their vocals of said themes.

h4. See also

* [[Kyou mo Dokokade Devilman]]

h4. External links

* The original series: "Jaguarman":[https://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm31854709], "Jaghern":[https://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm31883836] & "Jaguar Mask":[https://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm31892798]

title: 507th_joint_fighter_wing
body:
The 507th Joint Fighter Wing is a volunteer group previously called the Suomus Independent Volunteer Aerial Squadron. To many, they bear the nickname "Silent Witches" or, less flatteringly, the "Suomus Misfit Squadron" in reference to the reputation of some squad members. As per the name, it is stationed in Suomus. They are the subject of the '[[Strike Witches: Suomus Misfits Squadron]]" light novels.

The tag should ideally refer to most (5+) of the squadron together.

h6. Original members

title: strike_witches:_suomus_misfits_squadron
body:
A series of light novels in the [[World Witches Series]] franchise by Yamaguchi Noburo. Published in 3 volumes from 2006 to 2008, and received a reboot in 2018. It was the very first instalment in the franchise, back when it was known as Strike Witches

It stars the Suomus Independent Volunteer Aerial Squadron (later renamed the [[507th Joint Fighter Wing]]). In theory an elite international squad, most of its members were in fact sent there for bad behaviour, and as result it came to be known as the "Suomus Misfits Squad".

title: katharine_o'hare
body:
Character from [[Strike Witches: Suomus Misfits Squadron]].

A Pilot Officer from Liberion serving in the [[507th Joint Fighter Wing]]. Known as "Crasher O'Hare" due to her propensity fro crashing her Striker Unit (either by clumsiness or bad luck).

Her weapons include a M2 Heavy Machine Gun, a M1919 A6, a Breda-SAFAT 12.7 mm machine gun, and a Colt SAA Revolver. In her original desigin, her familiar is the Abyssinian cat, but this was later changed to a raccoon, and she's based on Butch O'Hare.

title: manchukuo
body:
A puppet state created by the empire of Japan after their invasion of northeastern China, also known as Manchuria. Manchukuo was created in 1932 as a republic but was changed to a constitutional monarchy in 1934 when last emperor of the former [[Qing dynasty]], [[aisin-gioro puyi|Puyi]] took over power. Manchukuo's capital was Hsinking (Xinjing) meaning "new capital" and is today known as Changchun. 

Manchukuo's motto was "Five Races Under One Union" (adapted from the motto of the Republic of China) which reflected the five largest ethnicities living in Manchuria: the Manchu people, Han Chinese, Mongol, Hui people and Koreans, this was also reflected in Manchukuo's flag. Although Manchukuo presented itself as a nation with the five races, many other smaller ethnic minorities were suppressed and murdered.  

Manchukuo was dissolved on August 18th, 1945 after Puyi abdicated on the 17th following the Soviet invasion of Manchuria that year.

h4. See also
* [[Manchukuo flag]]
* [[Manchurian imperial army]]

title: captain_america
body:
[i]An Avenger! And an icon to people everywhere; [b]Captain America[/b] is the definition of a true hero![/i]
---[b]Stan Lee[/b]

A [[Marvel]] superhero created by legendary comic book artists Joe Simon and [[Jack Kirby]].

[b]Captain America[/b], real name [[Steve Rogers]], used to be a skinny, short soldier who was given a serum during [[World War II]] that bestowed him with super human physical abilities above the peak of human potential. He is easily identified by his red-white-and-blue [[superhero costume]] and similarly designed circular shield which is made of Vibranium, a fictional metal that is rare and can reflect any and all attacks.

He is one of the most recognized members of [[Avengers (series)|The Avengers]].

h4. See also
* [[Red guardian (marvel)|]]
* [[Soldier Boy (The Boys)]]
other_names: キャプテン・アメリカ

title: sunny_splosion
body:
Sunny Splosion is an English-speaking [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] affiliated with [[Glitch Stars]] Generation 'Dreamers' since 15 February 2025. Reportedly debuted on 30 July 2022, and streamed previously as an [[Indie Virtual Youtuber]] prior to affiliating with Glitch Stars.

She has [[short hair|short]], [[streaked hair|streaked]] [[grey hair|grey]] and [[blonde hair|yellow]] hair, topped with 2 [[antenna hair|antennas]]. Her hair is long enough to reach [[hair between eyes|between]] her [[purple eyes|purple]]/[[pink eyes|pink]] eyes, forming [[crossed bangs]]. She wears a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]], [[grey shirt|grey]] [[crop top]] with [[cross-laced top|cross-laces]] (revealing her [[navel]] and [[midriff]]) and [[black pants]] held in place with a [[black belt]]. His outfit consists of a [[black coat]] with [[seigaiha]] wave print and his personal emblem on it with laundry symbols added, a [[grey hoodie]], [[black gloves]], [[yellow belt|yellow]] [[belt pouch]], [[black pants]] with a second yellow pouch on his left leg, a [[yellow ribbon]] on his right leg, grey socks with [[sayagata]] print, [[black footwear|black sneakers]], and [[earrings]] with yellow cloths displaying his personal emblem and the kanji 封 (Fu in "Fuma").

title: higanbana_no_saku_yoru_ni
body:
Lit. [i]On the Night the Red [[Spider Lily]] Blooms[/i]

A visual novel and 2010-2012 manga by [[Ryukishi07]] and 07th Expansion of [i][[Higurashi no Naku Koro ni]][/i] and [i][[Umineko no Naku Koro ni]][/i], with illustrations by Tsunohazu Ichirou, serialized in Fujimi Shobo's [i]Monthly Dragon Age[/i]. 

It originally began as [i]Gakkou Youkai Kikou: Dai-hachi Kaidan Boshuuchuu[/i] (学校妖怪紀行 第八怪談募集中), lit. [i]School Youkai Traveler's Guide: Recruiting the Eighth Kaidan[/i], a 2007 light novel serialized in Fujimi Shobo's [i]Dragon Age Pure[/i], with illustrations by [[Nishieda]], which ran for three chapters before being discontinued. 

It was then followed by the manga [i]Gakkou Youkai Kikou - You[/i] (学校妖怪紀行 ~葉~), with illustrations by [[Izumi Rei]], which was also serialized in [i]Dragon Age Pure[/i] in 2007 before ending after two chapters.

title: futaba_minato
body:
Futaba Minato is a Japanese [[cevio|CeVIO AI]] voicebank developed and distributed by Gasoline Alley, Inc. and released on December 2, 2022. The idea behind her character was to create a completely original voice synthesis character from scratch, with "youth (青春)" as her main theme.

Her voice is provided by Misawa Sachika and she is illustrated by [[hitoba]]. Minato has [[blue eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] with a [[blue hair|blue]] [[colored inner hair|inner tint]]. She wears a [[white dress|white]] [[sleeveless dress]], [[layered dress|layered]], with a [[brooch]] and a [[blue ribbon|blue]] [[gradient neck ribbon]]. Some accessories include [[hairclip|hairclips]], a [[wrist scrunchie]], and [[sneakers]].

title: kage_no_kuni_no_butoukai
body:
[b]Land of Shadows Battleground Blitz ~A Cat, a Bunny, and a Holy Grail War~[/b]
[quote]As humanity's final hope, Master is thrown into harsh battles almost daily. On one such day, Scáthach, a Heroic Spirit from the Age of Gods, forcefully Rayshifts Master to a place that resembles the Land of Shadows she rules.

"What you lack is experience fighting against enemy Masters...in short, experience in Holy Grail Wars!"

She was right. While Master may have overcome many hardships, they certainly do not have much experience fighting against other Masters. Most of their missions so far have focused on traveling to and investigating points of interest.

"Starting now, you will think with your Servant, fight with your Servant, and claim victory with your Servant! This mock Holy Grail War shall be known as the Grail Front!"

Her instruction is so harsh, even famous heroes flee her lessons with their tails between their legs! Using her crimson spear as a teacher's pointer, what kind of special lessons does Scáthach have in store for Master...?[/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on September 18, 2020 and on the NA server on August 22, 2022.

title: akatsuki_(akatsuki_en-eins)
body:
h5. [[Akatsuki Blitzkampf]]

A High class technical officer of the Imperial army. Believed to have died in the Arctic oceans at a critical time when the war was coming to its end, during the transportation of a new military unit from an allied country. Fifty years later, he returns alive and unchanged in appearance. Now wielding superhuman abilities, he resumes his mission.

h5. [[Under Night In-Birth]]

Guest character in [b]Under Night In-Birth[/b]. He gets involved in the Hollow Night while traveling to [[Mount Fuji]] to destroy the Blitz Motors. He fights many In-Births along the way, often times being mistaken for a [[cosplay|cosplayer]]. He apparently gets really [[hungry]] when ever he taps into his Blitz Motor.

title: turbo_granny_(dandadan)
body: The Turbo-Granny, a character of the manga series [[Dandadan]], is a well-known yokai that was previously within a tunnel located at Shono City until her confrontation with [[Ayase Momo]] and [[Takakura Ken (Dandadan)|]]. After having her powers sealed within [[Takakura Ken (Dandadan)|]], along with her consciousness being trapped inside a stuffed cat doll, the Turbo-Granny makes a deal with [[Ayase Momo]] to help [[Takakura Ken (Dandadan)|]] find his kintama in exchange for having her powers back.

title: akebono_(kancolle)
body: [[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Akebono[/i]. Character design by [[Drew (drew213g)|]], voiced by [[Hayasaka Kozue]]. She has [[purple eyes]] and [[very long hair|very long]] [[purple hair]] in a [[side ponytail]], plus a [[hair flower]] and [[hair bell]]. Her default outfit is shared with the other Special Types, consisting of a [[short_sleeves|short-sleeved]] shirt and [[blue_skirt|blue]] [[pleated_skirt]]. She also typically wears [[black socks|black]] [[kneehighs]] and [[loafers]] outside of her combat gear. Her [[rigging]] consists of her funnel-mast set worn like a backpack, a handheld 12.7 cm twin gun mount, and carried over a shoulder strap. Her shoes are armored, and she wears dual torpedo turrets on her thighs, like many in the [i]Fubuki-class[/i]. She refers to the [[Admiral (kancolle)|]] as a "[[Shitty Admiral_(phrase)|]]" and is seemingly always angry about something, stemming from her ill experiences during the war. In some fanworks, calling the admiral "shitty" is so ingrained in her, she even calls the admiral "shitty admiral" when she's in love, like other girls might say "darling". She's typically portrayed as a [[tsundere]] with almost no dere, at least not verbally, or a "bitter-tongued tsukkomi. Oftentimes, she's seen playing a big sister role to [[Ushio (kancolle)|]], who is often portrayed as the most childish and clumsy of the 7th Des Div. Along with the rest of the 7th DesDiv, Akebono has been one of the most frequent targets of limited-time special event artwork. h4. body:
A mysterious supporting character in [[Devil May Cry 4]], Gloria is a newcomer to the Order of the Sword, but whose true agenda is a mystery even to them. She has dark skin, blue eyes, silver-white hair and a white outfit that shows plenty of skin. She prefers dual daggers, and is unusually adept at killing demons with them.

[spoiler]She's an alter ego of [[Trish (devil may cry)|]].[/spoiler]

title: gambit
body: Gambit (Remy Étienne LeBeau) is a character appearing in American comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]], commonly in association with the [[X-Men]]. The character was created by writer Chris Claremont and artist Jim Lee. Drawn by artist Mike Collins, Gambit made his first appearances in The Uncanny X-Men Annual #14 (July 1990) and The Uncanny X-Men #266 (August 1990). Belonging to a subspecies of humans called mutants, Gambit can mentally create, control, and manipulate pure kinetic energy. He is also incredibly knowledgeable and skilled in card throwing, hand-to-hand combat, and the use of a bō. Gambit is known to charge playing cards and other objects with kinetic energy, using them as explosive projectiles.

title: walker_(robot)
body:
A type of bipedal (or multipedal) [[non-humanoid robot]] or [[mecha]] frequently used in [[science fiction]] media. 

They usually lack a head or arms and some have [[chicken]]-like legs. The [[AT-ST]] and [[AT-AT]] from [[Star Wars]] and the [[tripod_(mecha)|Tripods]] from [[War of the Worlds]] are arguably the most recognizable examples of this style of mecha design.

Do not confuse these for regular [[mecha]]s - if it's humanoid it's typically not a walker.

h4. Examples
* !post #7265868: An [[AT-ST]], the typical "chicken walker" style of walker
* !post #7071647: A [[Regult]], another "chicken walker" type
* !post #7190664: A [[Titan (c&c)|]], a "walking tank" style walker
* !post #4758111: An [[M1A4 Juggernaut]], a multipedal "spider" style walker


h4.  See Also:

title: akihabara_explosion!
body:
[b]Akihabara Explosion! ~The City of Wishes and the Sculptures Engraved with Love~[/b]
[quote]The most recent minute Singularity has been detected in none other than Akihabara... Yet this Akihabara feels slightly different than its historical counterpart.

Chaldea heads to Akihabara Tower Hall, which is believed to be the source of the anomaly, but are prevented from entering. They learn very quickly that shopping inside Akihabara Tower Hall is no cakewalk, for it has become a demonic realm where shopping neophytes are turned away. Only veteran shoppers are permitted within. To prove their shopping expertise in Akihabara, Protagonist and company head out to collection shopping points.

And thus an unprecedented mission, Operation: Shop till You Drop, begins! All members of Chaldea are mobilized!

Head into the digital sanctuary of Akihabara! It's time to splurge, no holds barred![/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on March 24, 2021 and on the NA server on March 17, 2023.

title: joy_(shenmue)
body:
Joy is a supporting character in the Sega video game series Shenmue. She first appears in the 2001 sequel Shenmue 2, where she assists the protagonist Ryo Hazuki navigate his way through Hong Kong and Kowloon Walled City in search of his father's killer. She has a brash, generally positive personality and is often seen riding a motorcycle around the city. It is implied she has a romantic interest in Ryo, which is not reciprocated. Joy appears briefly in Shenmue 3 during a phone conversation cameo.

Joy has a prominent role in the 2022 anime adaptation Shenmue the Animation, where her backstory is further expanded on. It is revealed she is the daughter of a Hong Kong cartel leader. Her mother was killed by Shenmue 2 antagonist and rival crime lord Don Niu during an attack on her father's business, leading to estrangement from her father.

title: ai_no_dendoushi_amor-chan_no_saint_valentino!
body:
[b]Amor-chan, the Preacher of Love's Saint Valentino! ~Chaldea Bitter Valentine's 2021~[/b]
[quote]One day, Master was greeted with a strange sight in the hallway: Servants who normally start arguing the moment they see each other are smiling and engaging in friendly conversation.

It is initially believed that this change in temperament was owed to Valentine's Day, but the situation takes a dark turn when beings that resemble Shadow Servants begin popping up all around Chaldea.

Master quickly goes to confront the new threats, but for every shadow defeated, a new enemy takes its place, leaving Master cornered. Just then, a mysterious new Servant arrives with advice for Master: the shadows can only be destroyed by love!

"Please give me your orders, Master. Please, test your strength as a Master and the strength of my love as you will!"[/quote]

title: little_big_tengu
body:
[b]Farewell to Kamakura ~Little Big Tengu~[/b]
[quote]"Hey there! I am the ultimate strategist and swordsman, renowned for generations the world over AND the onmyouji priest famous throughout the capital of Japan!"

A dark shadow suddenly assaults Chaldea, claiming to have come to punish her disciple Ushiwakamaru for misdeeds committed during her lifetime. When Ushiwakamaru claims ignorance, her furious mentor punishes her with a magical hammer called the Mallet of Fortune. The power of the hammer was supposed to make her reflect on her past actions...but instead she attacks Master and steals the hammer!

Now transformed into what was once known as "Overseer Yoshitsune," Ushiwakamaru flees into a Minute Singularity of her own making.

Chaldea's Master Rayshifts in pursuit, hoping to find the reason for her actions...[/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on January 20, 2021 and on the NA server on January 20, 2023. [[Kiichi Hogen (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: eikou_no_santa_claus_road
body:
[b]The Glorious Path to Santa Claus ~The Sealed Christmas Present~[/b]
[quote]Christmas season is upon Chaldea once again! This year, Karna has been appointed Santa, and as he diligently gives out presents (also known as roadwork) throughout the festively decorated Chaldea, every single gift mysteriously transforms into an unopenable black box! To determine the cause, Master and Karna Rayshift to a Singularity in the snowy mountains, where they encounter a mysterious Servant possessing tremendous power.

"Why do you impede my gift-giving? Answer me...evil dragon!"

Who is this mysterious Servant who transformed every Christmas present into black boxes, and what could they intend? To bring smiles backto everyone's faces, to restore Chaldea's presents to their original form...Karna's shining fist will blaze a trail through the holy night![/quote]

A limited time [[Christmas]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on December 16, 2020 and on the NA server on December 12, 2022. [[Karna (Santa) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

body:
[b]Valentine's 2020: A Not-So-Ordinary Valentine's ~Murasaki Shikibu and the Five Slaying Queens~[/b]
[quote]Valentine's Day is a cruel holiday.
Those who receive no chocolates are labeled as unattractive or unpopular, and so become the target of much ridicule.

Is being unpopular really such a crime? Is it not the popular ones who should be hated and treated as sinners? Won't somebody just give me some chocolates?!

As the cruel punishment of Valentine's Day hangs over the heads of those who have no chocolate to their name, a sparkling girl with love in her heart and an unpopular bearded man scurry about in search of chocolate![/quote]

title: aeae_no_shunpuu
body:
[b]The Aeaean Spring Breeze ~The Witch, Delightful Companions, and a New Adventure~[/b]
[quote]I'm leaving.
No, you're not.

The debate continued without end.
As tempers rose, arguments and even insults were exchanged.

...Or at least that was the bitter story of heartbreak... One from long ago...

The Greek island of Aeaea, said to be the home of a witch...
This is Master and company's destination in a mission to resolve a minute Singularity.
There, they meet a Servant who has been robbed of his memories.
Who took these memories from him, and what might they have contained...?

This is a story of a love that should have ended.

An expected reunion makes the queen witch's heart flutter once again.[/quote]

title: son_gohan
body:
The first son of [[Son Goku]] and [[Chi-Chi (dragon ball)|]] in [[Dragon Ball]]. He is named after Goku's adoptive grandfather [[Grandpa Gohan]].

Gohan is the first Half-[[Saiyan]] of the series, and as such he inherited the fighting prowess of his father while being less "battle eager" due to his mother. He is later on married with [[Videl]] and had a daughter named [[Pan (dragon ball)|]].

Like the other male members of the Goku family, Gohan is voiced by [[Nozawa Masako]].

title: ahnenerbe_shop_uniform
body:
The uniform worn by waiters and waitresses at the Ahnenerbe coffee shop in the metaverse created by Kinoko Nasu of [[Type-Moon]] fame (including series like [[Fate (series)|]], [[Kara no Kyoukai]]. [[Mahou Tsukai no Yoru]], [[Mahou Tsukai no Hako]], [[Tsukihime]], [[Carnival Phantasm]] and others). Ahnenerbe is actually a Magician's Box created by [[Kischur Zelretch Schweinorg]] that connect parallel worlds together so characters from different series can interact with each other.

Post #3923017 shows the uniform for both men and women. The female uniform has different colored aprons depending on the character.

The term [i]Ahnenerbe[/i] means "ancestral heritage" in German.

title: son_goku
body:
The main protagonist of the [[Dragon Ball]] series. He is married to [[Chi-Chi (dragon ball)|]] and has two sons named [[Son Gohan]] and [[Son Goten]].

Goku is a [[Saiyan]] born on planet Vegeta and raised on Earth. Capable of several different transformations including [[Kaiouken]], [[Super Saiyan]] [[Super Saiyan 1|1]], [[Super Saiyan 2|2]], [[Super Saiyan 3|3]], [[Super Saiyan 4|4]], [[Super Saiyan God]], [[Super Saiyan Blue]] and, ultimately, [[Ultra Instinct]].

His Saiyan name is "Kakarot", which is how [[Vegeta]] addresses him throughout the anime and manga. Some of his signature techniques are the [[Kamehameha (dragon ball)|]] and the [[Genki Dama]].

He is loosely based on [[Sun Wukong]] of the classical Chinese novel [i][[Journey to the West]][/i], whose name is translated as Son Goku in Japanese.

Goku's Japanese seiyuu is [[Nozawa Masako]], the current English dub voice actor is [[Sean Schemmel]] (though the character has gone through many different dub voice changes in the past), and his Latin American dub voice actor is Mario Castañeda.

In the early series, he possesses the [[ruyi jingu bang|Power Pole]] and the [[Flying Nimbus]].

title: sung_jin-woo

Sung Jin-Woo (성진우) is the main protagonist of the South Korean multimedia franchise [[Solo Leveling]]. Originally an infamously weak E-Rank Hunter, he got the chance of a lifetime when he was selected as the Player of the System, giving him the ability to grow stronger without limit. As a result, by taking advantage of the opportunities offered to him by the System, Jinwoo eventually rose to power as the new Shadow Monarch and the strongest hunter in the world.

title: kalina_(girls'_frontline)
body:
[[Girls' Frontline]] character. A logistics officer in the Griffin branch base, her main job is to coordinate resource movements for the [[Commander (girls' frontline)|]]. However, due to a lack of manpower in such a distant location, Kalina also carries out the duties of a secretary.

Her standard costume consists of a [[pleated skirt]], dress shirt, a tan [[jacket]], tactical [[gloves]] and [[high heel boots]]. Her [[thighhighs]] are [[mismatched legwear|mismatched]], with one being solid black and the other with black and white stripes.

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[orange hair]] made up into a [[side ponytail]].

Kalina has an obsession with money (or in the player's case, gems) and will encourage the player to spend at her in-game shop.

She is cheerful, passionate and casual by nature and is very friendly to the Commander. For the most part Kalina is diligent at her work, but in her private life she has a typical girlish side to her.

She returns in [[Girls' Frontline 2: Exilium]] [[aged up]] and wearing a black suit.

Voiced by [[Touyama Nao]].

title: futanari-chan_(akiamare)
body:
An [[original|original character]] by [[akiamare]] who is a [[futanari]].

She has [[blue eyes]] with usually [[heart-shaped pupils]], [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] styled with [[bangs]] and a [[hair ornament|hair accessory]] either being a [[hair ribbon|ribbon]] or [[hair bow|bow]]. She has [[large breasts]] and is usually drawn wearing a [[school uniform]] amongst other outfits.
